acy, recast: Accusers speak in detail about sexual-assault allegations|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/bill-cosbys-legacy-recast-accusers-speak-in-detail-about-sexual-assault-allegations/2014/11/22/d7074938-718e-11e4-8808-afaa1e3a33ef_story.html |work=The Washington Post |date=November 22, 2014 |accessdate=November 24, 2014}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=etonline_accuserlist>\n{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's Accusers: A Timeline of Sexual assault Claims (Updated)|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/154160_timeline_of_bill_cosby_sexual_assault_allegations/ |publisher=ET Online |date=August 21, 2015 |accessdate=September 30, 2015}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=salon_sandy>\n{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby and drugging: My 34-year-old secret|url=http://www.salon.com/2014/11/30/bill_cosby_and_drugging_my_34_year_old_secret/ |publisher=Salon |date=November 30, 2014 |accessdate=September 30, 2015}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=\"nymagexpose\"/>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=accusertable_sep3015>\n{{cite news|title=Another three women allege they were sexually assaulted by Bill Cosby|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/crime/bill-cosby-accused-sex-assault-3-women-article-1.2380493 |work=New York Daily News|date=September 30, 2015 |accessdate=September 30, 2015}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=accusertable_tirl>\n{{cite news|title=Cosby accuser Eden Tirl speaks out: 'I didn't wait to come forward'|url=https://www.yahoo.com/katiecouric/the-former-actress-says-she-was-pulled-off-the-set-126590667323.html|publisher=Yahoo!|date=September 30, 2015}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=accusertable_oct2315>\n{{cite news|title=Two more women accuse Bill Cosby of sexual misconduct|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/10/23/us-people-billcosby-idUSKCN0SH2HJ20151023 |agency=Reuters |date=October 23, 2015 |accessdate=October 23, 2015}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n<span style=\"display:none;\">\n<ref name=accusertable_ridgewaywhitedeer>\n{{cite news|title=Three more women accuse Bill Cosby of decades-old assaults|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-people-billcosby-idUSKCN0QH2JI20150812 |agency=Reuters |date=August 12, 2015 |accessdate=April 28, 2017}}\n</ref>\n</span>\n\n==Criminal investigations==\n===Constand case===\n====Unsealing of ''Constand v. Cosby'' deposition====\n\n{{main|Andrea Constand v. William H. Cosby, Jr.}}\n\nOn July 8, 2015, Constand and her attorney Dolores Troiani filed a motion to negate the [[confidentiality agreement]] in the 2005 case against Cosby, claiming Cosby had already engaged in \"total abandonment of the confidentiality portions of the agreement\" by way of the recent, sweeping denials of all allegations against him.<ref name=legalintelligencer>{{cite news|url=http://www.thelegalintelligencer.com/id=1202733285173/Plaintiff-Rebuts-Cosby-Allegation-of-Settlement-Breach?slreturn=20150826123020|title=Plaintiff Rebuts Cosby Allegation of Settlement Breach|publisher=The Legal Intelligencer|date=July 29, 2015|accessdate=September 26, 2015}}</ref><ref name=torontosun_constant>{{cite news|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2015/07/08/bill-cosby-sex-case-toronto-woman-speaks-to-sun|title= Bill Cosby sex case: Toronto woman speaks to Sun|work=Toronto Sun|date=July 8, 2015|accessdate=September 26, 2015}}</ref> A judge ruled that releasing the sealed documents was justified by Cosby's role as a \"public [[moral]]ist\" in contrast to his possible criminal private behavior.<ref name=MDale>{{cite news|last1=Dale|first1=Maryclaire|title=Cosby admitted in 2005 to getting sedatives to give to women he sought sex with|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/cosby-admitted-in-2005-to-getting-quaaludes-to-give-to-women-he-sought-sex-with/article25330387/|work=The Globe and Mail |location=Toronto |date=July 7, 2015 |accessdate=July 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAlthough some of the files from the Constand case had been unsealed, the transcript of Cosby's several [[Deposition (law)|deposition]]s was not among them. Instead, ''[[The New York Times]]'' had been able to obtain the complete deposition from a court reporting service that had been hired by Constand's attorney and released the document to the general public.<ref name=NYT72015>{{cite news|author1=Graham Bowley and Sydney Ember|title=Uncertainty on Whether Cosby Revelations Could Hurt Him in Court|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/21/business/uncertainty-whether-cosby-revelations-could-hurt-him-in-court.html |work=The New York Times |date=July 20, 2015 |access-date=July 21, 2015|quote=In a statement, The Times said it had obtained the transcript legally. \"The judge in the case had declined in 2005 to enter a confidentiality order making the depositions confidential so there was no court order sealing the testimony, then or now,\" it said. (The confidentiality agreement was between the parties to the law suit.) \"Once we obtained the transcript, we were free to report on Mr. Cosby's testimony.}}</ref> After it was discovered that the transcript of the deposition had been released, Cosby's lawyers filed a new motion in the case on July 21, 2015, asserting that Constand and Troiani may have orchestrated the release.<ref name=theguardian_sanctions>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jul/22/bill-cosby-sanction-accuser-sexual-assault-case|title=Bill Cosby calls for court sanctions against accuser in sexual assault case|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=July 22, 2015|accessdate=July 22, 2015}}</ref><ref name=Fox8_deposition>{{cite news|url=http://fox8.com/2015/07/22/bill-cosbys-lawyer-deposition-shouldnt-have-been-released-was-misinterpreted|title=Bill Cosby's lawyer: Deposition shouldn't have been released, was 'misinterpreted'|publisher=[[WJW (TV)|Fox8]]|date=July 22, 2015|accessdate=July 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn the court filing condemning the release of the deposition, Cosby's attorneys stressed that none of the testimony that was actually unsealed by a judge stated that he engaged in non-consensual sex or gave anyone Quaaludes without their knowledge or consent. \"Reading the media accounts, one would conclude that the Defendant has admitted to rape\", the document said. \"And yet the Defendant admitted to nothing more than being one of the many people who introduced Quaaludes into their consensual sex life in the 1970s.\" Cosby's lawyers further contended that a court reporting service hired by Constand had released the 2005 court transcript to the ''Times'', days earlier, in a \"massive breach of protocol\". The court reporters' code of ethics prohibits the release of testimony without all parties first being contacted.<ref name=\"theguardian_sanctions\"/><ref name=\"Fox8_deposition\"/>\n\nIn the deposition, Cosby denied any sexual assault of any women but admitted he had used [[sedative]]s to help gain their cooperation.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bowley |first=Graham |date=July 18, 2015 |title=Bill Cosby in his deposition said fame and drugs helped him seduce women |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/19/arts/bill-cosby-deposition-reveals-calculated-pursuit-of-young-women-using-fame-drugs-and-deceit.html |newspaper=The New York Times |location=New York |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> He testified that he had obtained Quaaludes from gynecologist Leroy Amar,<ref>{{cite news |last=Brittain |first=Amy |date=July 23, 2015 |title=When Bill Cosby wanted Quaaludes, he turned to this gynecologist |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/when-bill-cosby-wanted-quaaludes-he-turned-to-this-gynecologist/2015/07/23/1599a9be-2fe1-11e5-8f36-18d1d501920d_story.html |newspaper=The Washington Post |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> who knew Cosby had no intention of taking the drugs himself. Cosby instead intended to give them to women he wanted to have sexual relations with and admitted he had given the drug to at least one woman and other people.<ref>{{cite news |author=staff |date=July 19, 2015 |title=Excerpts From Bill Cosby's Deposition in 2005 and 2006 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/07/18/arts/bill-cosby-deposition-excerpts.html|newspaper=The New York Times |location=New York |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> Cosby admitted knowing it was illegal at the time to dispense the drug to other people. Amar would later have his [[medical license]] revoked in California and New York; he died in 2002.<ref name=\"Moghe\"/><ref name=Dale>{{cite news|last1=Dale|first1=Maryclaire|title=Cosby said he got drugs to give women for sex|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/6d90b1f473f147ed9f0048f9e9ac2287/apnewsbreak-cosby-said-he-got-drugs-give-women-sex|work=Associated Press|accessdate=July 7, 2015}}</ref>\n\n====2015 criminal charges====\n\nOn December 30, 2015, in [[Montgomery County, Pennsylvania]], Cosby was charged with three counts<ref>{{cite news |last=Woolf |first=Nicky |date=December 30, 2015 |title=Bill Cosby cuts a frail figure on a day many thought would never come |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/30/bill-cosby-appears-in-court-on-charges-indecent-assault-day-many-accusers-doubted-would-come |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=December 31, 2015}}</ref> of [[aggravated indecent assault]] on Constand as a result of a single incident alleged to have occurred at his home in [[Cheltenham Township]] on an unspecified date between mid-January and mid-February 2004 (referred to by media coverage as \"January 2004\"), according to the very detailed arrest warrant filed on December 15, 2015.<ref name=\"Kevin R. Steele\">{{cite web |url=http://www.montcopa.org/DocumentCenter/View/10048 |title=Police Criminal Complaint |author=Kevin R. Steele |date=December 15, 2015 |publisher=Montgomery County, Pa. |access-date=January 1, 2016}}</ref> These are the first criminal charges as a result of sexual assault allegations that have been made by many women against Cosby.<ref name=\"bigstory.ap.org\"/>\n\nCosby was [[arraignment|arraigned]] that afternoon without entering a plea; his bail was set at $1 million. Cosby surrendered his [[passport]], posted [[bail bond|bond]], and was escorted to the Cheltenham Township police station to be booked, fingerprinted, and photographed for a mug shot.<ref name=Castillo >{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/12/30/us/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-investigation-pennsylvania/ |title=Bill Cosby arraigned, doesn't enter plea |last1=Castillo |first1=Mariano |last2=Hanna |first2=Jason |date=December 30, 2015 |publisher=CNN |access-date=December 30, 2015}}</ref> The charges are based on Constand's statement to police of unwanted sexual contact, though not intercourse, in early 2004, that had been first reported to the [[Durham Regional Police Service]] near Constand's home in southern [[Ontario]], [[Canada]], on January 13, 2005;<ref name=\"Kevin R. Steele\"/> the report was forwarded to authorities in Pennsylvania.<ref name=\"The Associated Press\">{{cite news |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/latest-bill-cosby-charged-2004-case-36007715 |title=The Latest: Bill Cosby Charged With Sexual Assault |agency=Associated Press |date=December 30, 2015 |publisher=ABC News |access-date=December 30, 2015}}</ref> On February 17, 2005, the then-[[district attorney]], [[Bruce Castor]], had released a statement that charges would not be laid at that time.\n\nConstand launched a civil lawsuit against Cosby in 2005 which was settled by the defendant in July 2006, on a confidential basis. Some of the testimony from that case was unsealed in July 2015.<ref name=\"6abc.com\">{{cite web |url=http://6abc.com/news/bill-cosby-arraigned-on-sex-assault-charge/1140645/ |title=Bill Cosby Arraigned on Sex Assault Charge |last=Dale |first=Maryclaire |date=December 30, 2015 |publisher=WPVI |access-date=December 30, 2015}}</ref> Based on details revealed in this testimony, along with new interviews with certain witnesses, newly elected District Attorney Kevin Steele decided to file charges on December 30, 2015.<ref name=Castillo /> The criminal court documents allege<ref>{{cite news |last=Chokshi |first=Niraj |date=December 30, 2015 |title='Taste the wine': What prosecutors say Bill Cosby did, in graphic detail |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2015/12/30/you-are-a-very-sick-man-bill-cosbys-accuser-and-the-full-details-from-the-criminal-complaint/ |newspaper=The Washington Post |access-date=January 1, 2016}}</ref> that blue pills, said to be [[Benadryl]] by Cosby,<ref name=\"Kevin R. Steele\"/> were given to Constand, who had also been drinking wine during the January 2004 incident.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/bill-cosby-pennsylvania-charges-allegations-1.3384315 |title=Bill Cosby arraigned in court, charged with sex offence |agency=Associated Press |date=December 30, 2015 |publisher=CBC News |access-date=December 30, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Chokshi |first=Niraj |date=December 30, 2015 |title='Taste the wine': What prosecutors say Bill Cosby did, in graphic |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2015/12/30/you-are-a-very-sick-man-bill-cosbys-accuser-and-the-full-details-from-the-criminal-complaint/ |newspaper=The Washington Post |access-date=December 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCosby's attorney issued the following statement after the arraignment: \"The charge{{nbsp}}... came as no surprise, filed 12 years after the alleged incident and coming on the heels of a hotly contested election for this county's DA during which this case was made the focal point{{nbsp}}... We intend to mount a vigorous defense against this unjustified charge and we expect that Mr. Cosby will be exonerated by a court of law.\"<ref name=Castillo /> Attorneys for Cosby, on January 11, 2016, filed a motion to dismiss the sexual assault charges, stating that Castor's office had promised in 2005 that Cosby would not be prosecuted.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bowley |first=Graham |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/12/arts/television/bill-cosbys-lawyers-seek-dismissal-of-sexual-assault-charges.html|title=Bill Cosby's Lawyers Seek Dismissal of Sexual Assault Charges |newspaper=The New York Times |date=January 11, 2016 |accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> In testimony involving Cosby's motion to dismiss the charges, Castor defended his decision not to bring charges, citing among other things Constand's year-long delay in reporting the allegations, her continued contact with Cosby, and suggestions that she and her mother might have tried to extort the TV star.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://6abc.com/news/cosby-lawyer-says-comedian-was-assured-he-was-in-the-clear/1183142/ |title=Judge refuses to throw out sex assault case against Cosby |publisher=WPVI |date=February 3, 2016 |accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn February 3, 2016, Judge Steven O'Neill ruled \"there was no basis\" to dismiss the case based on Cosby's assertions. O'Neill scheduled a [[preliminary hearing]] for March 8.<ref>{{cite news|last=Cooper |first=Aaron |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/02/03/us/bill-cosby-andrea-constand-sex-assault-charges/ |title=Bill Cosby case: Judge says prosecution can go forward |publisher=CNN |date=February 3, 2016 |accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> On February 12, Cosby's legal team filed a notice of [[appeal]] seeking to give their arguments before the [[Superior Court of Pennsylvania]]. \"If Mr. Cosby is successful on appeal, the case would be terminated immediately,\" they wrote.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20160213_Cosby_launches_appeal__seeks_to_halt_case.html |title=Cosby launches appeal, seeks to halt case |work=Philadelphia Daily News |date=February 14, 2016 |accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> On March 1, the Superior Court issued an order temporarily staying Cosby's March{{nbsp}}8 preliminary hearing until it could rule on his appeal asking for the case to be dismissed.<ref>{{cite web|last=Weisensee |first=Nicole |url=http://www.people.com/article/bill-cosby-criminal-case-pennsylvania-court-temporary-hold |title=Bill Cosby Sex Assault Charges: Pennsylvania Court Halts Case |work=People |date=March 1, 2016 |accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn April 13, 2016, Cosby filed a motion with the Superior Court to re-seal the deposition from the original Constand lawsuit. His lawyers made a similar request in federal court in [[Massachusetts]] earlier, but that motion was denied by Judge David H. Hennessy, who likened these efforts to putting the \"toothpaste back in the tube\", since Cosby's testimony has already been in the news for months.<ref name=Cosby_files_Motion_Constand_deposition_suppress>{{cite news |url=http://www.pennlive.com/news/2016/04/bill_cosby_testimony_appeal_mo.html|title=Bill Cosby's attorneys want to put 'toothpaste back in the tube' |date=April 14, 2016 |publisher= PA Penn Live |access-date=April 14, 2016}}</ref> On April 25, the Superior Court announced that it refused to hear Cosby's appeal to have the case dismissed, lifted a temporary stay of the pre-trial hearing, and sent the case back to the original court.<ref name=Cosby_loses_appeal>{{cite news |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20160426_Cosby_loses_appeal__criminal_case_to_resume.html|title=Cosby loses appeal bid, criminal case to resume\n|publisher=Philly.com |access-date=April 25, 2016}}</ref> At the preliminary hearing on May 24, a judge found that there was enough evidence to proceed with a trial, despite the fact that Constand did not testify, which is allowed under Pennsylvania law. He set a pre-trial hearing for September 6. Cosby appealed this decision based upon the belief his legal team had the right to [[cross-examination|cross-examine]] the accuser; he lost this appeal on October 12. The [[Pennsylvania Supreme Court]] announced it would review the state law in a separate case, to which Cosby's lead attorney, Brian McMonagle, said he would try to add Cosby's case in hopes of having it thrown out.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/05/24/us/bill-cosby-hearing/|title=Bill Cosby to stand trial for assault charges, judge rules|publisher=CNN |date=May 24, 2016 |access-date=August 1, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/10/12/cosby-loses-latest-effort-to-get-charges-thrown-out.html|title=Cosby loses latest effort to get charges thrown out|publisher=Fox News |date=October 12, 2016 |access-date=October 12, 2016}}</ref> On September 6, 2016, Judge Steven O'Neill set a trial date for June 6, 2017.<ref name=\"Rappleye, Connor\">{{cite news |last=Rappleye |last2=Connor |first=Hannah |first2=Tracy |date=September 6, 2016 |title=Bill Cosby's Sex Assault Trial Set for June 5 |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/bill-cosby-scandal/bill-cosby-returns-court-ahead-sex-assault-trial-n643446 |publisher=NBC News |access-date=September 6, 2016}}</ref> On April 12, 2017, the Pennsylvania Supreme Court declined to hear Cosby's appeal to question Constand before the trial.<ref name=Cosby_loses_Pennsylvania_Supreme_Court>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby loses appeal to question accuser before trial|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/04/13/bill-cosby-loses-appeal-to-question-accuser-before-trial.html|agency=Fox News|date=April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\nCosby had faced a maximum of fifteen to thirty years in prison if found guilty on all three counts and a [[Fine (penalty)|fine]] up to $25,000.<ref name=\"Gibbons\">{{cite news |last=Gibbons |first=Margaret |date=September 3, 2016 |title=Bill Cosby's sex assault case inches closer to trial |url=http://www.buckscountycouriertimes.com/news/local/bill-cosby-s-sex-assault-case-inches-closer-to-trial/article_f18bac40-550d-5516-a264-aafc60dd7ba8.html |newspaper=Buck County Courier Times |access-date=September 4, 2016}}</ref> Cosby's trial started on June 5, 2017,<ref name=\"Rappleye, Connor\"/> and ended in [[mistrial]] on June 17.<ref name=mistrial/>\n\n===Judith Huth===\n\nOn December 16, 2014, after a 10-day investigation, Los Angeles prosecutors declined to file any charges against Cosby after Judith Huth claimed the comedian molested her around 1974 at the [[Playboy Mansion]]. Huth had met with Los Angeles police detectives for 90 minutes. In rejecting the case, prosecutors evaluated the charge Cosby would have faced in 1974. Prosecutors took into account legislative changes that extend the statute of limitations for certain crimes but found no way that Cosby could be legally prosecuted.<ref name=7online_molestation>{{cite news|title=Prosecutors Won't File Charges Against Bill Cosby for Child Molestation |url=http://7online.com/entertainment/bill-cosby-wont-be-charged-in-la-child-molestation-claim/439506/|agency=Associated Press|date=December 16, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Lili Bernard===\n\nOn April 30, 2015, Cuban-American visual artist Lili Bernard filed a sexual assault complaint against Cosby in New Jersey, a state that has no statute of limitations for sexual assault.<ref name=Bernard>{{cite news|title=Lili Bernard Files Sexual Assault Charges Against Bill Cosby|url=http://www.thehollywoodgossip.com/2015/05/lili-bernard-files-sexual-assault-charges-against-bill-cosby/|publisher=The Hollywood Gossip|date=May 4, 2015}}</ref> On July 1, 2015, prosecutors declined to prosecute Cosby because the alleged offense happened before 1996 (the year the law was changed to lift the statute of limitations).<ref name=inquisitor_not_face>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby Will Not Face Charges Over Drug And Rape Allegations Made By Former 'Cosby Show' Actress|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/2218110/bill-cosby-will-not-face-charges-over-drug-and-rape-allegations-made-by-former-cosby-show-actress/|publisher=Inquisitor|date=July 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Chloe Goins===\n\nFrom July through October 2015, the Los Angeles Police Department conducted a criminal investigation into Cosby's alleged sexual assault of then 18-year-old model Chloe Goins.<ref name=LAPD>{{cite news|title=LAPD investigating Bill Cosby's alleged sexual abuse of young model|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/07/07/chloe-goins-lawyer-says-criminal-investigation-into-bill-cosby-ongoing-unsealed/|date=July 7, 2015|publisher=Fox News Channel|access-date=August 31, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150830000118/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/07/07/chloe-goins-lawyer-says-criminal-investigation-into-bill-cosby-ongoing-unsealed/|archive-date=August 30, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> The following day, in a statement to ABC News, the LAPD said it will explore any sexual assault accusations against Cosby, including accusations for which the statute of limitations has expired,<ref name=abcnews_LAPD_Confirms>{{cite news|title=Open Criminal Investigation for Bill Cosby, LAPD Confirms|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/open-criminal-investigation-bill-cosby-lapd-confirms/story?id=32300228|work=Good Morning America|date=July 8, 2015}}</ref> and referred the case to the County District attorney's office.<ref name=la_da_review>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby Faces Criminal Charges for Alleged Sexual Assault in L.A.|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-chloe-goins-charges-1201607736/|work=Variety|date=October 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAs with nearly all other cases of alleged sexual misconduct by Cosby, the statute of limitations has expired on this 2008 case, according to most experts. Nonetheless, an investigation of the Goins allegations was opened because \"LAPD officials said there were many reasons to investigate sexual assault allegations that fall beyond those legal deadlines. Old accusations may lead investigators to more recent incidents with other victims\" and Goins would be allowed to testify if charges were laid in any other (more recent) cases.<ref name=\"Winton\">{{cite news |last=Winton |first=Richard |date=December 30, 2015 |title=Could L.A. be the next place where Bill Cosby faces assault charges? |url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-la-bill-cosby-allegations-venue-20151230-story.html |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |access-date=December 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCosby's former attorney Martin Singer has stated he would provide documentary evidence to the Los Angeles police that established Cosby was in New York on August 9, 2008, the date of the incident alleged by Goins.<ref name=\"cnn.com\">{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/01/16/us/cosby-denies-allegation/ |title=Cosby denies assaulting woman at Playboy Mansion in 2008 |last=Ellis |first=Ralph |date=January 16, 2015 |publisher=CNN |access-date=December 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn January 6, 2016, the Los Angeles District Attorney's office announced that no charge would be laid because they were \"blocked by the statute of limitations or lacked sufficient evidence\".<ref name=Almasy >{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/01/06/us/bill-cosby-no-charges-los-angeles/ |title=Bill Cosby won't be charged in two sexual assault cases in Los Angeles |last1=Casarez |first1=Jean |last2=Almasy |first2=Steve |date=January 6, 2016 |publisher=CNN |access-date=January 18, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Bowley >{{cite news |last=Bowley |first=Graham |date=January 6, 2016 |title=Bill Cosby Inquiries in California to Be Dropped |work=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/07/us/bill-cosby-inquiries-in-california-to-be-dropped.html |accessdate=January 8, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Criminal proceedings and trial No. 1==\n\nOn September 6, 2016, Judge Steven T O'Neill set a trial date in the case of ''Commonwealth of Pennsylvania vs. William H. Cosby Jr.'', in which Cosby is being tried for three counts of aggravated indecent assault of Andrea Constand. O'Neill set a trial date of June 5, 2017.<ref name=\"Rappleye, Connor\"/> The judge ruled that Cosby is blind and that he may need special accommodations during the proceedings.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby sex assault trial date set; Judge says comedian is blind|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/09/06/judge-bill-cosby-is-blind-may-need-accomodations-at-sex-assault-trial.html|publisher=Fox News|date=September 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn October 6, 2016, Cosby resumed his bid to have his sexual assault case thrown out, arguing that his due process rights were violated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/bill-cosby-argue-his-due-935555|title=Bill Cosby to Argue His Due Process Rights Are Being Violated|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20161007_Cosby_urges_judge_to_toss_sex-assault_case__citing_shaky_evidence__health.html|title=Cosby urges judge to toss sex-assault case, citing shaky evidence, health|publisher=philly.com}}</ref> On November 16, 2016, O'Neill denied the motion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msn.com/en-us/tv/celebrity/bill-cosby-delivered-a-legal-blow-again/ar-AAkn7Ah|title=Bill Cosby delivered a legal blow - again|publisher=msn.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117211903/http://www.msn.com/en-us/tv/celebrity/bill-cosby-delivered-a-legal-blow-again/ar-AAkn7Ah|archivedate=November 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\nCosby faced a maximum sentence of fifteen to thirty years in prison if found guilty on all three counts and a fine of up to $25,000.<ref name=\"Gibbons\"/>\n\n===Pretrial motions===\n====Evidentiary motions====\n\nOn September 6, 2016, the prosecution filed a motion to introduce 13 other accusers to show a method of operation. Cosby opposed the motion.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial/> On February 24, 2017, O'Neill ruled that, out of the other accusers that the prosecution wanted to introduce to show a pattern of alleged criminal sexual behavior by Cosby, only one would be allowed to testify.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_one_accuser_allowed>{{cite news|title=Judge: Only one other accuser can testify at Bill Cosby sex assault trial|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2017/02/24/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-trial-judge-rules-one-accuser-can-testify/98347388/|work=USA Today |date=February 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe prosecution also moved to introduce into evidence a recorded conversation between Constand's mother Gianna Constand and Cosby discussing the alleged assault. The defense moved to have the deposition from Andrea Constand's 2005 civil deposition thrown out. The judge said he would rule on all these motions at a later date.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial_1>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby sex abuse trial scheduled for 2017|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/09/06/us/bill-cosby-sex-abuse-hearing/|publisher=CNN|date=September 6, 2016}}</ref> On September 16, 2016, O'Neill ruled that the recorded call between Constand's mother and Cosby would be allowed to be played in court. In his ruling he said that since the call was recorded in Canada, which deems recordings lawful with consent from only one party, it would be admissible.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial_Recorded_Call>{{cite news|title=Judge: Phone Call With Accuser's Mother Can Be Played During Cosby Trial|url=http://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2016/09/16/phone-call-can-be-played-cosby-trial/|publisher=CBS PHILLY|date=September 16, 2016}}</ref> On December 5, 2016, O'Neill ruled that the deposition in the Constand civil case and any other evidence gathered by using it would be allowed into the trial.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial_Deposition_loses>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's Civil Deposition Testimony Can Be Used by Prosecutors in Criminal Trial, Judge Rules|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/bill-cosbys-civil-deposition-testimony-prosecutors-criminal-trial/story?id=43991862/|publisher=ABC News|date=December 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 28, 2017, Cosby's defense filed a motion stating that any mention of any other sexual offenses allegedly committed by Cosby should be excluded and that any of Cosby's admissions in his deposition about using Quaaludes or other women he had sex with should also be excluded, even though the judge ruled previously that all information in the deposition would be allowed in court.<ref name=Cosby_tries_to_get_part_of_deposition_sealed>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's lawyers ask to exclude testimony on other women, pills from sex-assault trial|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/bill-cosby-lawyers-exclude-testimony-assault-trial-article-1.3012268|work=Daily News|date=March 28, 2017}}</ref> On March 30, 2017, the prosecution opposed this motion and added that comments Cosby made in TV interviews with [[Larry King]] and in his 1991 book named ''Childhood'' about his quest for \"Spanish Fly\" showed that he was well aware of date rape drugs and that this should also be put into the trial as evidence.<ref name=prosecution_objects_to_get_part_of_deposition_sealed>{{cite news|first1=Hannah |last1=Rappleye |first2=Tracy |last2=Connor|title=Prosecutors Want Cosby Jury to Hear 'Spanish Fly' Comments|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/bill-cosby-scandal/prosecutors-want-cosby-jury-hear-spanish-fly-comments-n740706|publisher=NBC News|date=March 30, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn April 28, 2017, O'Neill ruled that the use of \"Spanish Fly\" and any other material from Cosby's book ''Childhood'' would not be allowed. He did however rule that his testimony about Quaaludes would be allowed. O'Neill also ruled that the amount of money paid in Constand's lawsuit settlement would be excluded.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial_Quaaludes_Allowed>{{cite news|title=Judge: Cosby jury can hear about quaaludes, not Spanish fly|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/judge-cosby-jury-hear-quaaludes-spanish-fly-47085749|publisher=ABC News |date=April 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Jury selection====\n\nOn December 30, 2016, Cosby's defense team filed a motion for a [[change of venue]] and sought a jury selection from a larger pool outside the county, arguing that any local jury pool would be tainted given negative media coverage of Cosby. On January 5, 2017, the prosecution wrote that the trial should stay in [[Montgomery County, Pennsylvania|Montgomery County]], but they would not object to a jury picked from outside the county.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Change_of_venue_motion>{{cite news|title=Cosby seeks change of venue as coming trial seems increasingly unavoidable|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2016/12/30/cosby-seeks-change-venue-coming-trial-seems-increasingly-unavoidable/96003412/|agency=Associated Press|date=December 30, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"montcopa.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.montcopa.org/ArchiveCenter/ViewFile/Item/3558 |title=IN THE COURT OF COMMON PLEAS OF MONTGOMERY COUNTY, PENNSYLVANIA - CRIMINAL DIVISION |date=December 30, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Change_of_venue_motion_Prosecution>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's Trial Shouldn't Move Location, Prosecutor Says|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7647592/bill-cosbys-trial-location|agency=Associated Press|date=January 6, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"montcopa.org\"/>\n\nOn February 27, 2017, O'Neill ruled that he would allow a jury from outside the county but the trial would remain in Montgomery County; he also ruled the jury would be sequestered.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Change_of_venue_motion_ruling>{{cite news|title=A Judge Has Rejected a Request to Move Bill Cosby's Trial, but Will Bring In Outside Jury|url=http://time.com/4685087/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-jury/|magazine=Time|date=February 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2017, the Pennsylvania State Supreme Court issued a one-paragraph order setting Allegheny County as the county from which the jury pool would be picked. Allegheny County, which includes Pittsburgh, is the state's second most-populous county.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Jury_pool_location>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby jury will be picked in Allegheny County|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/pennsylvania/Jury-for-Bill-Cosby-trial-to-come-from-Allegheny-County.html|agency=Philly.com|date=March 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2017, the defense asked the court to call up 2,000 people as potential jurors. They wished to mail the potential jurors a questionnaire so lawyers could winnow the field of potential jurors.<ref name=Cosby_2000_Jurors>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's lawyers ask to summon up to 2,000 potential jurors for his trial|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/Bill-Cosby-lawyers-jury-trial-Allegheny-County-Montgomery-county.html|publisher=Philly.com|date=March 20, 2017}}</ref> The prosecution objected to Cosby's defense team's requests as to the number of jurors to be questioned, the manner in which they were to be selected, and the timeframe for jury selection, saying Cosby was trying to get special treatment.<ref name=Cosby_2000_Jurors_Objection_Prosecution>{{cite news|title=Prosecutors fight Cosby bid to grill up to 2,000 potential jurors for trial|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/03/27/prosecutors-fight-cosby-bid-to-query-2000-potential-jurors/99702568/|work=USA Today |date=March 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn April 11, 2017, O'Neill denied the defense motions on screening jurors and ruled that jury selection would start on May 22 in Pittsburgh, using the usual procedures of law and lasting up to a week. There would be 12 jurors and six alternates. O'Neill also denied a request by the defense to get extra strikes.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Jury_selection_day>{{cite news|title=Jury Selection In Bill Cosby's Case Set For May 22 In Pittsburgh|url=http://pittsburgh.cbslocal.com/2017/04/11/bill-cosby-pittsburgh-jury-selection/|agency=CBS Pittsburgh|date=April 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn May 24, 2017, the jury selection process was completed. The jury consisted of one black woman, one black man, six white men, four white women and six alternates.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Jury_selected>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby jury selected|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/05/24/us/bill-cosby-jury-selected/|agency=CNN|date=May 24, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Jane Doe No. 6===\n\nJane Doe No. 6 is a witness for the prosecution and she was the only one of the 13 [[John Doe|Jane Does]] that O'Neil allowed to testify. She is a black woman who came forward in January 2015 under the alias \"Kacey\". She claimed that in 1996 Cosby gave her a drug and wine and sexually assaulted her.<ref name=Victim_Six>{{cite news|title=Court lets only one additional alleged victim testify in Bill Cosby sex-assault case|url=http://www.standard.net/National/2017/02/24/Court-lets-only-one-additional-alleged-victim-testify-in-Bill-Cosby-sex-assault-case|agency=Standard Examiner|date=February 24, 2017}}</ref><ref name=Rule_404a>{{cite news|title=Commentary: Bill Cosby's 'prior bad acts'\u2014what will a jury hear?|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/commentary/ct-bill-cosby-sexual-assault-case-jury-20160105-story.html|agency=Chicago Tribune|date=January 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Racial bias claims===\n\nIn a press appearance following a hearing in September 2016, Cosby's lawyers claimed for the first time that racial bias was to blame for the sex-assault charges against their client.<ref name=\"APClaim\">[http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/09/09/bill-cosbys-lawyers-claim-racism-for-first-time.html Bill Cosby's lawyers claim racism for the first time], Associated Press (September 9, 2016).</ref> In response, prominent [[criminal defense lawyer]] commentators, such as [[Mark Geragos]] and [[Carl E. Douglas]], stated that this assertion may be an effort to influence potential jurors.<ref name=\"APClaim\"/>\n\nThe defense criticized lawyer [[Gloria Allred]], who represents several of Cosby's accusers, stating that Allred's \"campaign against Mr. Cosby builds on racial bias and prejudice that can pollute the court of public opinion.\"<ref name=\"APClaim\"/> Allred responded by calling the claim \"desperate\". She said Cosby \"complains about racial bias but what about the African American women whom I represent who accuse him of sexual assault or rape and who refuse to remain silent about what they say they have suffered?\" and \"This is not an issue of racial bias. Instead, it is an issue of whether or not Mr. Cosby has committed acts of gender sexual violence.\"<ref>Michael Rothman & Andrew Wyatt, [http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/bill-cosby-arrives-court-sexual-assault-case/story?id=41891662 Bill Cosby's Lawyer Cites 'Racial Bias and Prejudice' Amid Sex Assault Allegations], ABC News (September 6, 2016).</ref>\n\n===Declaration of mistrial===\n\nOn June 17, 2017, O'Neill said the jurors were \"hopelessly deadlocked\" and declared a [[Mistrials|mistrial]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://uk.news.yahoo.com/bill-cosby-judge-declares-mistrial-153000452.html |title=Bill Cosby: Judge declares mistrial after jury says it is 'hopelessly deadlocked' in sexual assault case |work=[[The Independent]] |last=Mindock |first=Clark |date=June 17, 2017 |access-date=June 17, 2017}}</ref> Reports suggest that the jury deadlocked in a 10\u20132 vote in favor of convicting Cosby on counts{{nbsp}}1 (digital penetration without consent) and{{nbsp}}3 (drugged without knowledge or consent), and was 11\u20131 in favor of acquittal on count{{nbsp}}2 (that Constand was unconscious or unaware during the alleged assault).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://people.com/crime/bill-cosby-two-jurors-guilty-verdict/|title=Two Jurors Prevented a Guilty Verdict in Bill Cosby's Trial|work=People|first=Alexia|last=Fernandez|date=June 21, 2017|access-date=June 22, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn an account by NBC News reporter [[Tracy Connor]], an anonymous juror said that when the jury first told the judge it was deadlocked, on June 15, the votes on the three counts were 7\u20135, 5\u20137, and 5\u20136 with one abstention. Two days later, the vote on one of the counts was 10\u20132, but then several jurors changed their minds, making it a more even split again. It was described as a 'true deadlock'.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/amp/cosby-trial-juror-says-it-was-true-deadlock-n775666|title=Juror says Bill Cosby 'already paid his price'|publisher=NBC News}}</ref> On June 23, a juror told CNN the jury deadlock was caused in large part by confusion over the contradicting statements made by Andrea Constand during testimony.<ref name=cnncosby>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/06/23/us/bill-cosby-juror-speak/index.html|title=Bill Cosby juror speaks: 'We had no real new evidence'|author=Lawrence Crook III |author2=Walter Imparato |author3=Eric Levenson |date=June 23, 2017|publisher=CNN|access-date=June 24, 2017}}</ref> The juror, speaking anonymously, also said the prosecution presented \"no real new evidence\".<ref name=\"cnncosby\" />\n\nThe prosecution announced on the same day of the mistrial that they intended to retry the case.<ref name=mistrial>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/jun/17/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-case-ends-mistrial-hung-jury |title=Prosecutors vow to retry Bill Cosby after sexual assault case ends in mistrial |work=[[The Guardian]] |last1=Redden |first1=Molly|last2=Pengelly|first2=Martin |date=June 17, 2017 |accessdate=June 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Criminal proceedings and trial No. 2==\n\nOn July 6, 2017, Judge O'Neill set a trial date of November 6 for Cosby's second trial, and also said both the defense and prosecution must submit jury selection questions by October 30.<ref name=Second_trail_set>{{cite news |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/bill-cosbys-retrial-expected-begin-nov/story?id=48235703|title=Bill Cosby's retrial expected to begin on Nov. 6 |publisher=ABC News|date=July 6, 2017 |accessdate=July 6, 2017}}</ref> This was subsequently delayed because Cosby changed attorneys. On September 15, 2017, Judge O'Neill set a new trial date of April 2, 2018.<ref name=Second_trail_set2>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2017/09/15/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-retrial-pushed-to-2018-what-to-know.html|title=Bill Cosby sexual assault retrial pushed to 2018: What to know |publisher=FOX News |date=September 15, 2017 |accessdate=September 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Appeals Process===\n\nCosby's attorneys have filed an appeal for a new trial citing eleven judicial errors at his trial. The most serious error cited, according to experts, was the allowance of multiple 'bad act' witnesses by Judge O'Neill who the defense cited as \"too remote in time\" and \"too dissimilar\" to the charges in the trial. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/13/arts/television/bill-cosby-jail-appeal.html|title=Bill Cosby\u00e2\u20ac\u2122s Appeal Cites 11 \u00e2\u20ac\u02dcErrors\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 by Trial Judge|first=Graham|last=Bowley|date=December 13, 2018|publisher=|accessdate=January 20, 2019|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Bob Law, the chairman of the National Black Leadership Alliance, Cosby was convicted with no physical evidence supporting the charges, no corroborating witnesses, no medical records, no police reports, only accusations from events that occurred 30 years in the past. In a letter to NNPA Newswire, Law said \"...{{nbsp}}that is in opposition to the legal principle that the accuser cannot bring the action and also be the witness without any collaborating evidence.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Voice |first1=The Atlanta |title=Legal experts: Cosby should prevail on appeal |url=http://www.theatlantavoice.com/articles/legal-experts-cosby-should-prevail-on-appeal/amp/ |website=The Atlanta Voice {{!}} Atlanta GA News |accessdate=15 April 2019 |date=1 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Attorney changes and trial setting===\n\nOn August 22, 2017, Judge O'Neil granted Cosby's request to change attorneys. Cosby will now be represented by [[Thomas Mesereau]], who was the lead attorney in the 2005 acquittal at [[Michael Jackson]]'s child molestation trial. Kathleen Bliss and Lane Vines will also represent Cosby. The judge also agreed to postpone the trial until at least March 2018 and accepted the new attorney's request to keep the trial local instead of a change of venue like the first trial.<ref name=Second_trial_att_changes_etc>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/bill-cosby-scandal/bill-cosby-hires-tom-mesereau-who-won-acquittal-michael-jackson-n794551|title=Bill Cosby Hires Tom Mesereau, Who Won Acquittal for Michael Jackson|publisher=NBC News |date=August 21, 2017 |accessdate=August 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Key motions===\n\nIn January 2018, the prosecution asked that 19 other alleged victims be allowed to testify to show a pattern of similar conduct, which is allowed under Pennsylvania law. The last defense filed a motion to have the case dismissed, alleging that Constand did not make the phone calls when she said she did. The defense has also asked that a former coworker be allowed to testify to the fact that she said Constand had told her she could make up a story about sexual misconduct and then sue someone for it. The defense has also asked the case be dismissed on prosecutorial misconduct and claims the statute of limitations has expired as well.<ref name=January_motions>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/bill-cosby-team-files-motion-dismiss-sexual-assault-charges-article-1.3779766|title=Bill Cosby's legal team files motion to dismiss sexual assault charges|publisher=Daily News |date=January 25, 2018|accessdate=January 25, 2018}}</ref><ref name=January_motions2>{{cite news |url=https://www.nbcphiladelphia.com/news/local/Bill-Cosby-Attorneys-Ask-to-Have-Sexual-Assault-Case-Tossed-Ahead-of-Retrial-471187083.html|title=Bill Cosby's Attorneys Ask to Have Sexual Assault Case Tossed Ahead of Retrial|publisher=NBC News |date=January 25, 2018|accessdate=January 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Guilty verdict===\n\nOn April 26, 2018, a jury found Bill Cosby guilty of three counts of aggravated indecent assault against Andrea Constand. The Montgomery County district attorney, Kevin Steele, asked at this point that Cosby's $1{{nbsp}}million bail be revoked, suggesting that he owned a private plane and could flee. This prompted an angry outburst from Cosby, who shouted, \"He doesn't have a plane, you asshole!\"; Cosby was ultimately not ruled a flight risk.<ref name=\"Graham\">{{cite news|last1=Bowley|first1=Graham|last2=Hurdle|first2=Jon|title=Bill Cosby Is Found Guilty of Sexual Assault|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/arts/television/bill-cosby-guilty-retrial.html|work=The New York Times|date=April 26, 2018}}</ref> All three charges are felonies, punishable by up to 10 years in state prison each and up to a maximum of $25,000 fine each. Cosby's lawyers have said they \"definitely\" plan to appeal the charges.<ref name=\"Graham\"/> His sentencing hearing began on September 24, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/bill-cosby-scandal/judge-sets-sentencing-date-bill-cosby-s-sex-assault-case-n874576|title=Judge sets sentencing date for Cosby's sex assault case|last=|first=|date=|work=NBC News|access-date=September 25, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nOn September 25, Cosby was sentenced to three to ten years in prison.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-45644374|title=Cosby sentenced to prison for sex assault|last=|first=|date=September 25, 2018|work=BBC News|access-date=September 25, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> He was also ordered to pay the cost of the prosecution, $43,611, against him as well as a $25,000 fine.<ref>{{cite web|author=Levenson, Eric|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/09/29/us/bill-cosby-prison-whats-next/index.html|title=What's next for Bill Cosby\u2014in prison, in court and beyond|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=September 29, 2018|accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref> On that day he was placed in the Montgomery County Correctional Facility in [[Eagleville, Montgomery County, Pennsylvania|Eagleville, Pennsylvania]], and moved to the [[Pennsylvania Department of Corrections]] [[SCI Phoenix]] in [[Skippack Township, Pennsylvania]] hours afterward.<ref>{{cite web|author=Wagner, Meg|author2=Brian Ries|author3=Jessie Yeung|author4=Eric Levenson|url=https://edition.cnn.com/us/live-news/bill-cosby-sentencing/index.html|title=Bill Cosby sentenced to 3 to 10 years|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=September 25, 2018|accessdate=September 26, 2018|quote=On Tuesday afternoon, Bill Cosby{{nbsp}}... He was also fined $25,000 plus the costs of prosecution.}}</ref>\n\n==Civil lawsuits against Cosby==\n\nAs of November 13, 2015, there were nine lawsuits pending against Cosby. Huth and Goins are both suing the actor for damages related to their alleged sexual assaults. Although the statute of limitations has run out for most other accusers to sue directly for their alleged assault, multiple accusers have filed [[defamation]] lawsuits claiming that Cosby had kept calling them liars throughout 2014. Dickinson, Hill, Ruehli, and McKee have filed individual lawsuits. Green, Serignese, Traitz, Bowman, Tarshis, Moritz, and Leslie are also involved in a combined lawsuit against Cosby. Most lawsuits that are active are currently on hold awaiting the outcome of his criminal trial. Some are still allowed to file motions and depose witnesses, with the exception of Cosby himself. However, most judges have indicated that a civil trial will not take place until after the criminal trial is held.\n\nIn 2005, Constand sued Cosby. The parties settled the case on confidential terms in 2006. In July 2015, after portions of the sealed deposition were released, Cosby released a statement saying the \"only reason\" why he settled \"was because it would have been embarrassing in those days to put all those women on the stand, and his family had no clue.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/bill-cosby-deposition-reveals-he-806963|title=Bill Cosby Deposition Reveals He Gave Women Quaaludes for Sex|last=Gardner|first=Eriq|date=July 6, 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> During summer 2015, both Cosby's legal team and Constand's lawyer Troiani filed motions accusing the other party of having broken the confidentiality agreement that was part of the 2006 settlement.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thelegalintelligencer.com/id=1202733285173/Plaintiff-Rebuts-Cosby-Allegation-of-Settlement-Breach |title=Plaintiff Rebuts Cosby Allegation of Settlement Breach |last=McLellan |first=Lizzy |date=July 29, 2015 |publisher=The Legal Intelligencer |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> The primary issue alleged by Cosby was that a court reporter released the full transcript of his deposition, blaming Troiani for this act<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/article/bill-cosby-accuser-andrea-constand-gay-court-filing |title=Bill Cosby's Original Accuser Andrea Constand Calls Him a 'Narcissist' Who Missed Cues That She's Gay |last= Ehrich Dowd |first=Kathy |last2=Weisensee Egan |first2=Nicole |date=July 28, 2015 |work=People |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> and seeking sanctions against Troiani.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/article/bill-cosby-admits-affairs-drugs-deposition-released |title=Bill Cosby Admits and Defends His Extramarital Affairs, Giving Women Drugs, in Newly Released Court Documents |last=Carlson |first=Adam |date=July 19, 2015 |work=People |access-date=January 3, 2016 }}</ref> A federal judge had unsealed portions of the evidence from the 2005 lawsuit, but that did not include Cosby's statements made [[under oath]].<ref>{{cite news |author=no by-line (Tribune wire reports) |title=Cosby lawyers: Release of deposition broke settlement terms |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/ct-bill-cosby-lawyers-20150723-story.html |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |location=Chicago, Illinois |date=July 23, 2015 |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe significance of the availability of the deposition is that it contains admissions made by Cosby about his tactics in dealing with other women, including the use of \"powerful sedatives [including Quaaludes] in a calculated pursuit of young women\", according to a ''New York Times'' summary.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bowley |first=Graham |date=July 18, 2015 |title=Bill Cosby in Deposition said drugs and fame helped him seduce women |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/19/arts/bill-cosby-deposition-reveals-calculated-pursuit-of-young-women-using-fame-drugs-and-deceit.html?hp&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&module=photo-spot-region&region=top-news&WT.nav=top-news&_r=1 |newspaper=The New York Times |location=New York, USA |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> The transcript of the full testimony was obtained by ''Times'' from a court-reporting service, where it was publicly available. The significance of the availability of Cosby's deposition from the Constand case is that plaintiffs in other cases against Cosby, such as Green, et al. defamation suit,<ref>{{cite news |last=Bowley |first=Graham |date=July 20, 2015 |title=on Whether Cosby Revelations Could Hurt Him in Court |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/21/business/uncertainty-whether-cosby-revelations-could-hurt-him-in-court.html |newspaper=The New York Times |location=New York |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> might be allowed by judges to use the transcript's contents as evidence now that its contents are widely known in the public.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lexislegalnews.com/articles/2291/judge-denies-cosby-s-discovery-motion-over-release-of-sealed-deposition |title=Judge Denies Cosby's Discovery Motion Over Release Of Sealed Deposition |author=Mealey's |date=September 9, 2015 |publisher=LexisNexis |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThirty-three of the accusers are being represented by Allred.<ref name=\"Allred_33_AllegedVictims\"/> One accuser, Dickinson, is represented by Allred's daughter, [[Lisa Bloom]].<ref name=cnn_dickinson_lawsuit>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/05/20/us/bill-cosby-sued-by-dickinson/|title=Bill Cosby sued for defamation by Janice Dickinson|publisher=CNN|date=May 21, 2015|accessdate=September 25, 2015}}</ref> On December 11, 2015, Allred stated in an interview with ''Philadelphia'' magazine that more alleged victims would be coming forward. She said, \"More women have contacted me who have not yet spoken out publicly, some of whom may do so in the future and some of whom have chosen not to do so. They wanted me to know the information that they had so it would be of assistance to us and our victim. There are definitely more women who wish to speak out in the future who allege that they are victims of Mr. Cosby.\"<ref name=\"Allred_number_accusers_more_coming_forward\">{{cite web|last1=Fiorillo|first1=Victor|title=Gloria Allred on Bad Men, Feminism, and Leaving Philly Behind|url=http://www.phillymag.com/news/2015/12/11/gloria-allred-bill-cosby/|accessdate=December 11, 2015|date=December 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Andrea Constand===\n\nConstand filed a civil claim in March 2005, with thirteen women as potential witnesses if the case went to court.<ref name=cnn/><ref name=WPost/> Cosby settled out of court for an undisclosed amount in November 2006.<ref name=cnn/> In a July 2005 ''[[Philadelphia Daily News]]'' interview, Beth Ferrier, one of the anonymous \"Jane Doe\" witnesses in the Constand case, alleged that in 1984 Cosby drugged her coffee and she awoke with her clothes partially removed.<ref name=\"MyUser_Foxnews.com_November_19_2014c\"/> After learning that charges were not pursued in the case, Green, the only publicly named woman in the prior case, came forward with allegations in February 2005 that Cosby had drugged and assaulted her in the 1970s.<ref name=WoolfGuardian/><ref name=philadelphiamagazine/><ref>{{cite news |last= Carter|first= Bill|date= November 14, 2014|title= Cosby Is Off Another Show as Rape Accusations Swirl|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/15/business/media/appearance-by-bill-cosby-with-david-letterman-canceled-as-rape-allegations-swirl.html|newspaper= The New York Times|location= |accessdate= November 16, 2014}}</ref> Cosby's lawyer said he did not know her and the events did not happen.<ref name=cnn2014/> It was revealed in 2018, in motions filed in Cosby's second criminal trial, that Cosby had settled with Constand for $3.5 million.<ref name=Settlement_Disclosed>{{cite news |last= Brown|first= Stacy|date= March 10, 2018|title= Bill Cosby paid Andrea Constand $3.5M in 2006 settlement|url= https://pagesix.com/2018/03/10/bill-cosby-paid-andrea-constand-3-5m-in-2006-settlement/|newspaper= PageSix|location= |accessdate= March 10, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Tamara Green, ''et al.''===\n\nGreen filed a lawsuit against Cosby and his representatives in December 2014, claiming that the continued denials amounted to publicly branding her as a liar, resulting in defamation of character.<ref name=\"green_lawsuit\">{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/article/bill-cosby-accuser-tamara-green-files-defamation-suit|title=Bill Cosby Accuser Tamara Green Files Defamation Lawsuit|work=People|date=December 10, 2014|access-date=September 25, 2015}}</ref> Green's lawsuit was filed in Cosby's home state of Massachusetts. In January 2015, the lawsuit was amended to allow fellow accusers Traitz and Serignese to be added as co-plaintiffs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chaikinandsherman.com/Personal-Injury-Blog/2015/January/Partner-Joseph-Cammarata-Files-Amended-Defamatio.aspx|title=Partner Joseph Cammarata Files Amended Defamation Complaint Against Bill Cosby|publisher=Chaikin and Sherman}}</ref> Martin Singer had released a statement specifically targeting Traitz after she posted allegations against Cosby on [[Facebook]] in November, calling her story \"ridiculous\", \"absurd\", and \"utter nonsense\".<ref name=\"people_singer_traitz\">{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's Lawyer Slams New Accusations as 'Utter Nonsense'|url=http://www.people.com/article/cosby-lawyer-slams-new-accusations|access-date=September 24, 2015|work=People|date=November 20, 2014}}</ref> No such denials were leveled explicitly at Serignese, but she claims the sweeping denials against all Cosby's accusers included her and have damaged her reputation as well.<ref name=\"green_lawsuit_amended\">{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/article/bill-cosby-defamation-lawsuit-linda-joy-traitz-therese-serignese|title=Two Other Accusers Joining Tamara Green's Defamation Lawsuit Against Bill Cosby|work=People|date=January 5, 2015|access-date=September 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn October 20, 2015, [[American International Group|AIG]] filed legal papers to try to put a stay on the [[litigation]], pending a court declaration of whether the insurance company had a [[duty to defend]] Cosby as well as pay for any actual damages won. AIG Property Casualty Company claimed that Cosby's policy did not cover the liability he is currently facing in the lawsuit\u2014but that they have nonetheless been funding Cosby's legal defense \"at a considerable cost\".<ref name=aig_October20>{{cite news|url=http://www.thewrap.com/bill-cosbys-insurance-company-wants-accusers-lawsuit-put-on-hold/|title=Bill Cosby's Insurance Company Wants Accusers' Lawsuit Put on Hold|publisher=The Wrap|date=October 20, 2015|access-date=October 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn November 13, 2015, it was reported that four more women\u2014Bowman, Tarshis, Moritz, and Leslie\u2014had joined the lawsuit as additional plaintiffs. Bowman, Tarshis, and Leslie are co-represented by Chicago attorney Michael Bressler. Lawyers for Cosby declined to comment.<ref name=4_Women_Join_Suit>{{cite news|url=http://abc7.com/news/4-more-women-join-defamation-lawsuit-against-bill-cosby/1084477/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151115235123/http://abc7.com/news/4-more-women-join-defamation-lawsuit-against-bill-cosby/1084477/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=November 15, 2015 |title=4 More Women Join Defamation Lawsuit Against Bill Cosby |publisher=WABC |date=November 13, 2015 |access-date=November 16, 2015 }}</ref> On December 14, Cosby filed a countersuit for defamation against all the plaintiffs, claiming that they had \"malicious, opportunistic and false and defamatory accusations of sexual misconduct against him\". He also claims each defendant \"knowingly published false statements and accusations\".<ref name=Cosby_counter_sues>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/bill-cosby-defamation-suit-accusers_566f06b3e4b0fccee16f4df8|title=Bill Cosby Sues Seven Of His Accusers For Defamation|publisher=The Huffington Post|date=December 14, 2015|access-date=December 14, 2015}}</ref> Cosby asked the court to award him unspecified damages and to require that public [[retraction]]s be made by the women.<ref name=Ellis >{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/12/14/us/bill-cosby-sues-accusers/ |title=Cosby sues 7 accusers for defamation, seeks damages and retractions |last=Ellis |first=Ralph |date=December 14, 2015 |publisher=CNN |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn February 19, 2016, Cosby's wife [[Camille Cosby|Camille]] was deposed by plaintiffs after unsuccessfully attempting to stop the deposition. U.S. Magistrate Judge [[Mark G. Mastroianni]] ruled that she could [[Spousal privilege|refuse to answer questions about private conversations]] with her husband.<ref name=Camille_ordered_Deposition>{{cite news|url=http://www.masslive.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2016/02/bill_cosby_wife_to_be_deposed.html|title=Bill Cosby's wife to be deposed Monday|publisher=MassLive|date=February 19, 2016|access-date=February 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Camille_ordered_2nDeposition>{{cite news|url=http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/arts-and-life/cosbys-wife-slated-to-give-deposition-in-defamation-case-369615391.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223101813/http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/arts-and-life/cosbys-wife-slated-to-give-deposition-in-defamation-case-369615391.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 23, 2016|title=Camille Cosby deposed in defamation case, returns next month|work=Winnipeg Free Press|date=February 22, 2016|access-date=February 23, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Camille_ordered_2nDeposition_Delay>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/camille-cosbys-2nd-deposition-postponed-until-april-18-204056011.html;_ylt=A0LEV77CzuJWWSUArL4PxQt.;_ylu=X3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw-- |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312001330/http://news.yahoo.com/camille-cosbys-2nd-deposition-postponed-until-april-18-204056011.html%3B_ylt%3DA0LEV77CzuJWWSUArL4PxQt.%3B_ylu%3DX3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw-- |url-status=dead |archive-date=March 12, 2016 |title=Camille Cosby's 2nd deposition postponed until April 18 |agency=Associated Press |date=March 10, 2016 |access-date=March 10, 2016 }}</ref> A transcript of the \"extremely contentious\" deposition was released in May 2016; Camille relied heavily on the marital privilege in refusing to respond to many questions.<ref name=\"CullinsReporter\">Ashley Cullins, [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/bill-cosby-lawsuit-wifes-dramatic-896144 Camille Cosby's Dramatic Deposition Transcript Unsealed], ''The Hollywood Reporter'' (May 20, 2016).</ref> The deposition was interrupted twice as the parties called U.S. District Judge David H. Hennessy to resolve disputes. After the deposition was halted, the court ordered Camille to sit for a second deposition.<ref name=\"CullinsReporter\"/>\n\nLawyers representing the alleged victims planned on deposing [[Quincy Jones]], who, as a friend and collaborator of Cosby for more than 50 years, may have had information vital to the plaintiffs' case.<ref name=Quincy_Jones_Deposition>{{cite news|url=http://www.masslive.com/news/index.ssf/2016/03/bill_cosby_accusers_plan_to_de.html|title=Bill Cosby accusers seek to depose music producer Quincy Jones in abuse case|publisher=MassLive|date=March 1, 2016|access-date=March 1, 2016}}</ref> In addition to Jones, plaintiffs intend to depose or subpoena documents from [[William Morris Endeavor]], Cosby's former attorneys Singer and Schmitt, and his publicist David Brokaw.<ref name=Plaintiff>>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/bill-cosby-libel-accusers-want-depose-quincy-jones-050034691.html;_ylt=A0LEVyHjeNhWIpwAzqRXNyoA;_ylu=X3oDMTEyaDkyMWp1BGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDQjE3OTNfMQRzZWMDc2M-|title=Bill Cosby Libel Accusers Want to Depose Quincy Jones, WME|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=March 1, 2016|access-date=March 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 21, 2016, Judge Anita Brody granted some access to the case file of Constand's lawyer, even though she settled in a confidential agreement with Cosby in 2006. However, Brody did limit the release of the case file to materials pertaining to the seven women plaintiffs and other witnesses.<ref name=Constand_settlement_partially_released>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/biz/news/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-andrea-constand-1201735198/|title=Judge Grants Bill Cosby Accusers Access to Andrea Constand's Case File|work=Variety|date=March 21, 2016|access-date=March 21, 2016}}</ref> On September 28, Cammaratta filed a motion stating that Cosby violated rules of [[civil procedure]]. The motion asked for the judge to rule that Cosby was personally responsible for the defamation said by his spokespeople and the publication of such materials; and that he should also be liable for causing the plaintiffs' emotional distress from these comments.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/tv/bill-cosby-accusers-ask-court-rule-admitted-liability-164406139.html|title=Bill Cosby Accusers Ask Court to Rule He Admitted Liability for Spokespersons' Statements|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=September 28, 2016|access-date=September 28, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Janice Dickinson===\n\nDickinson brought forth a similar defamation lawsuit against Cosby in May 2015, filed in California. According to Bloom, \"Calling Dickinson a liar is a defamatory statement under the law{{nbsp}}... and that's the mistake Bill Cosby made.\"<ref name=\"cnn_dickinson_lawsuit\"/> Later court filings included sworn statements from friends and colleagues who confirmed that Dickinson provided a consistent story for many years about her alleged abuse. [[Pablo Fenjves]], Dickinson's [[ghostwriter]], as well as former [[ReganBooks]] president [[Judith Regan]], both asserted that Dickinson came forward with her allegations for her 2002 autobiography, but they were not included in the book because ReganBooks' parent company [[HarperCollins]] was afraid of being sued by Cosby.<ref name=ladailynews_dickinson>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailynews.com/general-news/20150924/let-us-depose-bill-cosby-say-janice-dickinsons-lawyers|title=Let us depose Bill Cosby, say Janice Dickinson's lawyers|work=Los Angeles Daily News|date=September 24, 2015|accessdate=September 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn November 2, 2015, Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Debre Katz Weintraub ruled Cosby and Singer must give a deposition despite their efforts to have the case thrown out (Singer is not named as a defendant in the case). The ruling stated Dickinson's lawyers could seek answers only as to whether the denials were made maliciously, and Cosby and Singer could assert [[attorney\u2013client privilege]] and refuse to answer some questions.<ref name=dickinson_deposition>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/judge-orders-cosby-deposition-janice-dickinson-lawsuit-171745138.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151104131537/http://news.yahoo.com/judge-orders-cosby-deposition-janice-dickinson-lawsuit-171745138.html |url-status=dead|archive-date=November 4, 2015|title=Judge orders Cosby deposition in Janice Dickinson lawsuit|agency=Associated Press|date=November 2, 2015|accessdate=November 2, 2015}}</ref> Singer was scheduled to be deposed November 19 in Los Angeles, with Cosby's deposition occurring on November 23 in [[Boston]].<ref name=dickinson_deposition_nov23>{{cite news|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/175819_bill_cosby_s_deposition_janice_dickinson_defamation_case_to_take_place_on/|title=Bill Cosby's Deposition in Janice Dickinson Defamation Case Scheduled to Take Place on Nov. 23|publisher=ET Online|date=November 11, 2015|accessdate=November 11, 2015}}</ref> On November 12, a California appeals court temporarily halted an order requiring them to testify. Both parties are required to provide information by the end of the month to state their cases as to why or why not the deposition should proceed. \"We are confident that once the Court of Appeals hears full argument on the issues it will allow the deposition of Mr. Cosby and his attorney to go forward,\" Bloom wrote in an email.<ref name=Deposition_Delayed_dickinson>{{cite news|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/8620422041ff4c719824ed8cf2fc3eaf/appeals-court-temporarily-halts-upcoming-cosby-deposition|title=Appeals court temporarily halts upcoming Cosby deposition|work=Associated Press|date=November 12, 2015|accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> Singer announced that he was planning on \"pursuing claims against Janice Dickinson and Lisa Bloom after I prevail in this action.\"<ref name=singer_plans_action_dickinson>{{cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2015/11/bill-cosby-marty-singer-defamation-lawsuit-janice-dickinson-response-1201632462/|title=Bill Cosby Ex-Attorney Marty Singer Plans Legal Action Against Janice Dickinson|publisher=Deadline Hollywood|date=November 21, 2015|accessdate=November 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nDickinson later amended her complaint to name Singer as a co-defendant, alleging that after she made her allegations on [[CNN]], he prepared four press releases denying that Cosby drugged and raped her, and calling the woman's allegations \"fabricated\" and \"an outrageous defamatory lie\". Singer was later replaced as Cosby's counsel by Christopher Tayback of [[Quinn Emanuel Urquhart & Sullivan|Quinn Emanuel]].<ref name=dickinson_sues_singer>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bill-cosbys-attorney-added-janice-842083|title=Bill Cosby's Former Attorney Added to Janice Dickinson's Defamation Lawsuit (Report)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 18, 2015|access-date=November 18, 2015}}</ref> In February 2016, Judge Weintraub granted a motion by the defense to dismiss Singer as a defendant in the lawsuit.<ref name=Singer_dismissed_dickinson>{{cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/celebrity/news/bill-cosby-ex-lawyer-dismissed-janice-dickinson-lawsuit-180831741.html?ref=gs|title=Bill Cosby's Ex-Lawyer Dismissed From Janice Dickinson Lawsuit|publisher=The Wrap|date=February 9, 2016|access-date=February 9, 2016}}</ref> On March 29, Weintraub denied Cosby's motion to dismiss the case, allowing the case to proceed to a jury trial. Shortly after the ruling, Dickinson said, \"I want Bill Cosby in court, I want him to stand under oath.\"<ref name=Cosby_loses_stay_dickinson>{{cite news|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/entertainment/articles/2016-03-29/judge-to-consider-fate-of-dickinson-lawsuit-against-cosby|title=A judge says she won't dismiss model Janice Dickinson's defamation lawsuit against Bill Cosby|agency=Associated Press|date=March 29, 2016|accessdate=March 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn November 21, 2017, in a major blow to both Cosby and Singer, a California appeals court reversed two other courts' decisions to remove Singer as a co-defendant and added him back. In their ruling they stated that Singer and Cosby's anti-[[SLAPP]] motion was meritless.<ref name=CosbySinger_loses_appeal_dickinson>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/janice-dickinson-big-win-bill-cosby-defamation-suit-article-1.3649560|title=Janice Dickinson gets big win in Bill Cosby defamation suit|agency=Associated Press|date=November 21, 2017|accessdate=November 21, 2017}}</ref> In March 2018, after a last-ditch effort to get the case against Cosby and Singer dismissed, the [[California Supreme Court]] declined to intervene and hear arguments on the case.<ref name=CosbySinger_Supreme_Court_dickinson>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/bill-cosby-loses-appeal-janice-dickinson-defamation-lawsuit-article-1.3876128|title=Bill Cosby loses appeal in Janice Dickinson's defamation lawsuit|agency=Daily News|date=March 15, 2018|access-date=March 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Judith Huth===\n\nIn December 2014, Huth filed a lawsuit alleging sexual assault in 1974 at the [[Playboy Mansion]] when she was 15 years old.<ref name=Payne>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/12/03/showbiz/bill-cosby-allegations|title=Woman sues Bill Cosby for alleged sexual assault in 1974, when she was 15|publisher=CNN|date=December 3, 2014 |last=Payne |first=Ed |access-date=December 3, 2014}}</ref> It is one of two active lawsuits against Cosby directly alleging sexual assault. Even though the incident occurred more than forty years previously, California laws allow alleged child sexual abuse victims to bring their cases forward as an adult.<ref name=huth_lawsuit_sol>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3970055/bill-cosby-judy-huth-deposition|title=Why the New Case Against Bill Cosby Is Different|work=Time|date=July 23, 2015|access-date=October 19, 2015}}</ref> Cosby is countersuing both Huth and her attorney Marc Strecker for legal fees.<ref name=Cosby_counter_suit>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-30343324|title=Bill Cosby: Comic counter-suing over sex allegations|publisher=BBC News|date=December 5, 2014|access-date=December 5, 2014}}</ref> Cosby's attorney contends Huth and her attorney engaged in an [[extortion]] attempt before filing a suit. Singer's claim is made in a notice of [[demurrer]]. He also is seeking sanctions against Huth and Strecker.<ref>{{cite web|first=Ted|last=Johnson|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/cosby-attorney-says-accuser-tried-to-extort-money-before-filing-suit-1201371298|title=Cosby Attorney Says Accuser Tried to Extort Money Before Filing Suit|work=Variety|date=December 4, 2014|accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn August 4, 2015, a [[Los Angeles Superior Court]] judge ordered Cosby to give a sworn deposition in the lawsuit.<ref name=Time_underage>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/3986843/bill-cosby-sexual-abuse-underage-molestation-judy-huth-playboy-celebrities|title=Bill Cosby to Give Deposition in Playboy Mansion Underage Sex Abuse Lawsuit|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=August 5, 2015 |first=Alissa |last=Greenberg |accessdate=August 6, 2015}}</ref> Another judge refused to dismiss Huth's suit against Cosby<ref>{{cite news|first=Emily|last=Yahr|title=Bill Cosby sues seven of his sexual-assault accusers for defamation|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2015/12/14/bill-cosby-sues-seven-of-his-sexual-assault-accusers-for-defamation/|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=December 14, 2015|access-date=January 23, 2016}}</ref> and required him to provide a deposition, which was held on October{{nbsp}}9 in Boston and lasted 7.5 hours; no further details have been made public. The deposition was sealed until at least December 22, 2015.<ref name=huth_deposition>{{cite news|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2015/10/12/bill_cosby_deposition_in_judy_huth_suit_could_be_unsealed_after_december.html|title=New Cosby Deposition Could Be Unsealed in December|publisher=Slate|date=October 12, 2015|accessdate=October 19, 2015}}</ref> Allred announced that she would be seeking to depose Cosby again.<ref name=Allred_seeks_second_deposition>{{cite news|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/entertainment/celebrities_gossip/20151011_WENN_Judy_Huth_s_lawyer_wants_second_deposition_of_Bill_Cosby.html| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151013130421/http://www.philly.com/philly/blogs/entertainment/celebrities_gossip/20151011_WENN_Judy_Huth_s_lawyer_wants_second_deposition_of_Bill_Cosby.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=October 13, 2015|title=Judy Huth's lawyer wants second deposition of Bill Cosby|work=Philadelphia Daily News|date=October 12, 2015|accessdate=October 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\nHuth was scheduled to give her deposition for Cosby's attorneys on January 29, 2016.<ref name=\"Allred_number_accusers_more_coming_forward\"/>{{Update inline|date=April 2016}} However, on March 30, Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Craig D. Karlan granted a temporary delay of Cosby's second deposition and any further depositions of Huth. Judge Karlan did, however, rule that both sides could continue depositions of other people. Allred said she and partner John West planned to take depositions from other women who claim they were abused by Cosby when they were underage, and others.<ref name=Cosby_2nd_depo_huth_postponed>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/03/30/bill-cosby-2nd-deposition-in-sexual-battery-case-delayed-by-judge/|title=Bill Cosby's 2nd deposition in sexual battery case delayed by judge|publisher=Fox News|date=March 30, 2016|access-date=March 30, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331000251/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2016/03/30/bill-cosby-2nd-deposition-in-sexual-battery-case-delayed-by-judge/|archive-date=March 31, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Allred was scheduled to give a deposition of Hill, who has claimed Cosby sexually assaulted her when she was 16 years old, on April 8. Allred also announced that she would be deposing [[Hugh Hefner]] sometime in April.<ref name=Hefner_and_Hill_huth_deposed>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/hugh-hefner-asked-testify-bill-cosby-assault-case-article-1.2582787|title=Hugh Hefner will be asked to testify in sexual battery suit against Bill Cosby|work=New York Daily News |date=March 30, 2016|access-date=March 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn April 14, 2016, Cosby's lawyers filed a motion to dismiss Huth's lawsuit claiming that she changed her timeline regarding her \"delayed discovery\" of psychological injury or illness related to the alleged abuse.<ref name=Cosby_tries_to_dismiss_Huth_lawsuit>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/bill-cosby-child-sex-abuse-claims-tossed-judge-article-1.2601787|title=Bill Cosby wants child sex abuse claims tossed by judge|work=New York Daily News|date=April 14, 2016|access-date=April 14, 2016}}</ref> On April 26, Judge Kaplan refused to dismiss the majority of Huth's lawsuit; however, he did dismiss a \"negligent infliction of emotional distress\" claim. \"The court is not, at this time, willing to dismiss plaintiff's potentially meritorious claims against defendant based upon mistakes attributable to her former counsel,\" Karlan wrote. Allred said, \"We are very happy that the Court agreed and we will continue to vigorously fight for a just result for our client.\" Cosby's spokesperson, Monique Pressley, did not immediately comment on the decision.<ref name=Cosby_tries_to_dismiss_Huth_lawsuit_loses>{{cite news |url=http://www.seattletimes.com/nation-world/judge-rejects-cosbys-bid-to-dismiss-underage-sex-abuse-case|title=Judge rejects Cosby's bid to dismiss underage sex abuse case|work=Seattle Times|date=April 26, 2016|accessdate=April 26, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn September 20, 2016, it was revealed that one of the thirteen prosecution witnesses in the criminal trial is alleged Cosby victim Margie Shapiro. Allred filed a motion in the Huth civil case to have the deposition of Shapiro postponed until after the criminal trial. Allred stated she believed the defense would try to use the deposition against Shapiro to find discrepancies in the upcoming trial. Cosby attorney Angela Agrusa opposed this motion.<ref name=Cosby_Criminal_Trial_Civil_Case_postpone_deposition>{{cite news|title=Sexual abuse lawsuit against Cosby takes backseat to criminal case|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-people-cosby-idUSKCN11Q2PP|publisher=Reuters |date=September 20, 2016}}</ref> On June 27, 2017, Judge Kaplan set a trial start date for July 30, 2018.<ref name=Cosby_Huth_trial_date_set>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby Will Return to Court for Civil Suit Alleging He Sexually Assaulted Teen Girl at the Playboy Mansion|url=http://people.com/crime/bill-cosby-civil-suit-allegedly-molested-teen-playboy-mansion/|work=People|date=June 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Chloe Goins===\n\nOn October 6, 2015, Goins filed a lawsuit against Cosby.<ref name=Goins_Lawsuit>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3261374/Bill-Cosby-sued-sex-assault-Playboy-Mansion-inside-statute-limitation-faces-quizzed-oath-federal-court-model-s-claims.html?ITO=1490&ns_mchannel=rss&ns_campaign=1490|title=Bill Cosby is sued over 'sex assault' at Playboy Mansion inside statute of limitation - and faces being quizzed under oath in federal court about model's claims|work=Daily Mail|date=October 6, 2015 |last=Parry |first=Ryan |accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref> In her complaint, she stated that Cosby had assaulted her, causing her to suffer \"emotional distress\", \"psychiatric trauma\", and impairment of her education. Goins's lawyer, Spencer Kuvin, said his client's number-one priority was that the truth come out and Cosby be criminally prosecuted.<ref name=\"Goins_Lawsuit\"/> Singer stated he would provide documentary evidence to the LAPD that established Cosby was in New York on August 9, 2008, the date of the alleged incident.<ref name=\"cnn.com\"/> Although the prosecutor's office had considered filing criminal charges, the charges were dropped because the statute of limitations had expired and a lack of sufficient evidence.<ref name=Almasy />\n\nIn February 2016, Goins dismissed her lawsuit without prejudice.<ref name=Goins_Lawsuit2>{{cite news | url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-case-deposition-chloe-goins-dismissal-gloria-allred-1201694982/ | title=Bill Cosby Faces 2nd Deposition In Sexual Assault Case; Another Accuser Drops Suit | publisher=Deadline Hollywood | date=February 2, 2016 | last=Patten | first=Dominic | accessdate=February 2, 2016}}</ref> In May 2016, she refiled the suit, adding Hefner as a co-defendant.<ref name=Goins_Lawsuit_Hefner_Cosby>{{cite news | url=https://thinkprogress.org/cosby-accuser-calls-hugh-hefner-a-conspirator-adds-him-to-sexual-battery-lawsuit-e50a436a4152#.d6m7vq1is| title=Cosby Accuser Calls Hugh Hefner A 'Conspirator', Adds Him To Sexual Battery Lawsuit| publisher=ThinkProgress | date=May 18, 2016 | accessdate=May 18, 2016}}</ref> The judge denied Cosby's request to dismiss and set the trial to start sometime in June 2018.<ref name=Goins_Lawsuit_Scheduled>{{cite news| url=http://www.phillyvoice.com/amid-criminal-case-cosby-fighting-lawsuits-by-10-w/| title=Amid criminal case, Cosby fighting lawsuits by 10 women| publisher=Philly Voice| date=June 14, 2017| accessdate=June 14, 2017| url-status=dead| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614163711/http://www.phillyvoice.com/amid-criminal-case-cosby-fighting-lawsuits-by-10-w/| archivedate=June 14, 2017| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Renita Hill===\n\nHill claims that Cosby gave her a bit part on television, funded her college education and pledged to assist her career, all while sporadically sexually abusing her from 1983 to 1987. In October 2015, she filed a defamation suit against Cosby, Singer and Camille Cosby, alleging defamation, [[false light]], and [[intentional infliction of emotional distress]].<ref name=Renita_Hill_Lawsuit>{{cite web|last1=Silver|first1=Jonathon|title=Baldwin Borough woman who alleges Bill Cosby drugged and molested her files defamation suit|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/news/nation/2015/10/14/Baldwin-Borough-woman-sues-Bill-Cosby-alleging-that-comedian-drugged-and-molested/stories/201510140194 |date=October 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 14, 2015}}</ref> Cosby's attorneys [[Removal jurisdiction|removed]] the case from state to federal court and moved the court to dismiss the suit in late December 2015, arguing that Cosby's denials were opinions protected under the [[First Amendment]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Ove |first=Torsten |date=December 30, 2015|title=Baldwin woman defends federal defamation suit against Bill Cosby|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/local/city/2015/12/29/Baldwin-woman-defends-federal-defamation-suit-against-Bill-Cosby/stories/201512290158|newspaper=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|location=Pittsburgh, PA|access-date=December 30, 2015}}</ref> Hill's attorneys responded that Cosby's denials were published facts and hence are defamatory and not covered by First Amendment protections.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mandak |first=Joe |date=December 29, 2015|title=Attorneys for Pittsburgh-area Bill Cosby sex accuser defending defamation lawsuit|url=http://www.thespec.com/news-story/6212271-attorneys-for-pittsburgh-area-bill-cosby-sex-accuser-defending-defamation-lawsuit|newspaper=The Spectator|location=Hamilton, Ontario, Canada|access-date=December 30, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe U.S. District Court dismissed the suit \"with prejudice\" in January 2016, meaning the suit cannot be re-filed. Judge Arthur Schwab decided that statements made by Cosby and his attorneys were opinions protected by the First Amendment.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kontos|first=George|date=January 21, 2016|title=Pittsburgh woman's defamation suit against Bill Cosby is thrown out|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2016/01/21/pittsburgh-womans-defamation-suit-against-bill-cosby-thrown-out/79121412|newspaper=USA Today|location=Virginia, USA|access-date=January 21, 2016}}</ref> In April 2016, Hill filed an appeal with the [[U.S. Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Kontos|first=George|date=April 22, 2016|title=Pa. accuser appeals dismissal of Cosby lawsuit|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2016/04/22/another-pa-accuser-refiles-cosby-lawsuit/83391064|newspaper=USA Today|access-date=April 22, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Kristina Ruehli===\n\nOn November 9, 2015, Ruehli filed a defamation lawsuit against Cosby for denying her claims of rape. Ruehli's allegations against Cosby date back the furthest, with claims that he assaulted her in 1965. She claimed Cosby's vehement denials leveled against the numerous accusers in 2014 were grounds for defamation. Her complaint states, in part, \"It is one thing for an accused sexual assailant to remain silent and allow the legal process, or public opinion, to run its course, but it is quite another for him to unleash his agents to deny that he attacked the plaintiff and other women, to invite others to republish his statements, and to brand them as unreliable liars.\" In an account from ''The New York Times'', Ruehli has dropped her lawsuit without prejudice as of June 24, 2016.<ref name=ruehli_suit>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/11/09/us-people-cosby-idUSKCN0SY2OW20151109#WKr1T1Kj8T1mM7ux.99|title=Alleged rape victim sues Bill Cosby for defamation|agency=Reuters|date=November 9, 2015|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Katherine McKee===\n\nOn December 22, 2015, McKee, a former girlfriend of the late entertainer [[Sammy Davis Jr.]], sued Cosby for defamation over claims he and his attorney made about her allegation of being raped by Cosby in a [[Detroit]] hotel room in the early 1970s. Judge Mastroianni dismissed the lawsuit on February 16, 2017, on the basis of the landmark Supreme Court case ''[[New York Times Co. v. Sullivan]]'' in 1964, which required a higher standard to show the intent of malice towards a [[public figure]] to qualify as defamatory, and that given that her lawsuit, McKee was a [[public figure|limited public figure]].<ref name=McKee_Lawsuit>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/16/us/cosby-defamation-case-dismissed|title=Defamation lawsuit against Bill Cosby dismissed|publisher=CNN|date=February 16, 2017|accessdate=February 16, 2017}}</ref> Mckee appealed, but a federal appeals court refused to reverse Mastroianni's decision to dismiss the lawsuit on December 18, 2017.<ref name=McKee_Lawsuit_appeal>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/newswires/entertainment/court-refuses-revive-defamation-suit-bill-cosby-article-1.3572742|title=Court refuses to revive defamation suit against Bill Cosby|work=New York Daily News|date=October 18, 2017|accessdate=October 18, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019014941/http://www.nydailynews.com/newswires/entertainment/court-refuses-revive-defamation-suit-bill-cosby-article-1.3572742|archivedate=October 19, 2017}}</ref> On October 8, 2017, McKee's appeal was again dismissed; Judge Sandra Lynch cited \"McKee took concerted steps meant to influence the public's perception of whether Cosby was, in fact, a sexual predator,\" thus rendering herself a public figure. In January 2018, The [[U.S. Court of Appeals for the First Circuit]] refused to rehear her case in a full court hearing.<ref name=McKee_Lawsuit_appeal_denied>{{cite news|url=https://pagesix.com/2018/01/03/court-wont-rehear-defamation-case-against-bill-cosby/|title=Court won't rehear defamation case against Bill Cosby|work=New York Daily Associated Press|date=January 3, 2018|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> On petition to the Supreme Court, the Court denied to hear the case in February 2019, re-asserting that the ''New York Times Co.'' decision was properly applied at all levels.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/supreme-court/justice-clarence-thomas-criticizes-supreme-court-landmark-press-freedom-ruling-n973176 | title = Justice Clarence Thomas criticizes landmark Supreme Court press freedom ruling | first = Pete | last= Williams | date = February 19, 2019 | accessdate = February 19, 2019 | work = [[NBC News]] }}</ref>\n\n==Related litigation==\n===Suit against Cosby attorney===\n\nOn November 16, 2015, it was reported that accusers Tamara Green and Barbara Bowman filed a joint lawsuit against John Schmitt, one of Bill Cosby's lawyers. In November 2014, Schmitt released a statement reading, \"Over the last several weeks, decade-old, discredited allegations against Mr. Cosby have resurfaced. The fact they are being repeated does not make them true. Mr. Cosby does not intend to dignify these allegations with any comment.\" This statement was also posted to the front page of Cosby's official website. Green and Bowman contend that this widely circulated statement amounted to branding them as liars, resulting in emotional distress and other damages.<ref name=\"johnschmitt_lawsuit\"/>\n\n===Insurance coverage dispute===\n\n[[AIG]] Property Casualty Company, Cosby's homeowner's insurance, has tentatively agreed to pick up Cosby's legal costs for the Tamara Green, et al. case in Massachusetts, as well as for Janice Dickinson's case in California, over whether these women were defamed when Cosby's representatives denied the occurrence of sexual misconduct. But the insurer has also filed lawsuits related to both cases, aiming for [[declaratory relief]] that it is not responsible.\n\nCosby's homeowners insurance does cover him for \"personal injury\", which is defined in his policy as including \"bodily injury\"; \"shock, emotional distress, mental injury\"; \"invasion of privacy\"; and \"defamation, libel, or slander\". However, the policy contains an exclusion for \"sexual, physical or mental abuse\", setting the stage for a potentially novel legal battle over whether a defamation claim about the denial of sexual abuse is covered.<ref name=\"AIG_Lawsuit\"/>\n\nIn September 2015, Cosby filed a motion to either dismiss AIG's lawsuit or put it on hold. Cosby's attorneys argued that AIG was acting against Cosby's best interests and that fighting both the lawsuits from the accusers as well as from his insurance company would drain his resources.<ref name=reuters_idUSKCN0RF29D20150915>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/09/15/us-cosby-aig-idUSKCN0RF29D20150915|title=Bill Cosby seeks to dismiss AIG insurance lawsuit|agency=Reuters|date=September 15, 2015|access-date=September 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn October 9, 2015, AIG filed a response, calling Cosby's motion \"bizarre and possibly unique in the entire history of American jurisprudence\", criticizing Cosby's lawyers for referencing irrelevant case law from other states, and saying that if the court sided with Cosby, it \"would amount to a wholesale abandonment of this Court's jurisdiction, all for no apparent reason.\"<ref name=aig_october15>{{cite news|url=http://www.lexislegalnews.com/articles/3122/bill-cosby-s-motion-to-dismiss-is-bizarre-possibly-unique-insurer-argues|title=Bill Cosby's Motion To Dismiss Is 'Bizarre', 'Possibly Unique', Insurer Argues|publisher=Lexis Legal News|date=October 9, 2015|accessdate=October 20, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn November 13, 2015, California Federal Judge Beverly O'Connell granted Cosby's motion to dismiss in the Dickinson case and concluded that AIG had a duty to defend. In her opinion, O'Connell looked at the \"arising out of\" exclusion noted above and declares the meaning is ambiguous. \"The Court finds that both Plaintiff's broad interpretation and Defendant's narrow interpretation of 'arising out of' are reasonable{{nbsp}}... The sexual misconduct exclusion could reasonably be read to require that Dickinson's claims merely relate to sexual misconduct, or that Dickinson's claims be proximately caused by the sexual misconduct\", she wrote.\n\nSince ambiguous terms are interpreted in favor of finding coverage, Cosby prevailed. O'Connell gave a second independent reason for finding in Cosby's favor. She looked at the Dickinson complaint and concluded that there are allegations independent of sexual misconduct. \"For example, allegations that Defendant 'intentionally drugged' Dickinson 'even though he knew that she had been in a rehab center for addiction a few months before' could reasonably be interpreted as independent of sexual misconduct, and therefore, within the Policies' coverage{{nbsp}}... Similarly, the Dickinson Complaint alleges that Defendant's statements contain numerous implications about Dickinson, including the implication that 'Dickinson has copied the claims made publicly by other women against Defendant' and 'the implication that Ms. Dickinson's rape disclosure is a lie and that therefore she is a liar'\", she wrote. As courts impose coverage in a \"mixed\" action, Cosby prevailed here as well but this ruling does not apply to the Massachusetts case, where AIG and Cosby are still fighting to determine who is liable.<ref name=Cosby_Dismisses_AIG_Dickinson>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/bill-cosby-scores-victory-against-insurance-company-203210562.html;_ylt=A0LEV7rmh0dWcyEATL0PxQt.;_ylu=X3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw--|title=Bill Cosby Scores Victory Against Insurance Company|date=November 13, 2015|accessdate=November 13, 2015}}</ref> AIG plans to appeal this ruling.<ref name=Cosby_AIG_Appeal_Dickinson>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/why-aig-s-home-insurance-is-covering-bill-cosby-s-legal-costs-200246340.html;_ylt=A0LEVjs5KOhWhwIAEi0PxQt.;_ylu=X3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw--|title=Why AIG is paying Bill Cosby's legal costs|date=March 14, 2016|access-date=March 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nA Massachusetts federal judge, Mark G. Mastroianni, denied Cosby's bid to dismiss or pause the AIG suit on December 14, 2015. This judge, also responsible for the Green et al. defamation suit vs. Cosby, denied the insurance company's motion to pause that case.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.law360.com/articles/738046/cosby-can-t-nix-or-pause-aig-defamation-coverage-suit|title=Cosby Can't Nix Or Pause AIG Defamation Coverage Suit|last=Godoy|first=Jody|date=December 15, 2015 |publisher=Law360 |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Gloria Allred vs. Cobb-Marietta Coliseum, ''et al.''===\n\nOn November 18, 2015, Gloria Allred announced she was suing [[Cobb County, Georgia]]; Cobb-Marietta Coliseum; and Michael Taormina for violating her first amendment rights when she was denied entry to Cosby's stand-up comedy performance on May 2, 2015, at the [[Cobb Energy Performing Arts Center]] in Atlanta. Allred participated in a protest outside of the venue, but had also purchased a ticket to the show. Nevertheless, local police officers told her she would be arrested for trespassing if she entered the theater. Allred said Cosby's team coordinated with security and police to deny entry to individuals they had placed on a list of \"agitators\". Cobb-Marietta Coliseum is the name of the company that organized the show, and Taormina is its managing director. The police officers are employed by Cobb County.{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}\n\n\"Performers should not be able to commandeer a police force (as Bill Cosby's representatives appeared to do) in order to exclude individuals from the performance because they have a different viewpoint than the performer has\", Allred said. She sought a court order to prohibit what she calls the venue's \"censorship policy on admissions\".<ref name=allred_cobb_co>{{cite news|url=http://www.courthousenews.com/2015/11/18/lawyer-says-she-was-barred-from-cosby-show.htm |title=Lawyer Says She Was Barred from Cosby Show |publisher=Courthouse News Service|date=November 18, 2015|access-date=November 18, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn September 8, 2016, Allred reached a settlement with the defense. They agreed to pay Allred $40,000, along with a promise not to block any future customers from attending any public event held at the Coliseum.<ref name=allred_cobb_co_settlement>{{cite news|url=http://radiotvtalk.blog.myajc.com/2016/09/09/gloria-allred-wins-cobb-energy-bill-cosby-concert-protest-case/ |title=Gloria Allred wins Cobb Energy Bill Cosby concert protest case|publisher=Myagc|date=September 8, 2016|access-date=September 8, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Andrea Constand vs. Bruce Castor===\n\nOn October 26, 2015, Andrea Constand filed a federal lawsuit against former Montgomery County District Attorney Bruce Castor for defamation. Constand is being represented by her original 2006 ''Constand vs Cosby'' attorney Dolores Troiani.<ref name=Contand_sues_Castor>{{cite news|url=http://www.phillymag.com/news/2015/10/26/bruce-castor-lawsuit-andrea-constand-bill-cosby/|title=Bill Cosby Accuser Andrea Constand Sues Former D.A. Bruce Castor|publisher=News + Opinion|date=October 26, 2015|access-date=October 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nCosby's lead criminal lawyer in Pennsylvania is fighting a subpoena related to his $2,500 donation to the ex-prosecutor who says he had promised Cosby he would never be charged. Lawyer Brian McMonagle co-hosted a political fundraiser for former District Attorney Bruce Castor early last year{{When|date=January 2019}} but said it took place months before he joined Cosby's defense team in September. Constand's lawyer now wants McMonagle to detail any ties between his office and Castor, including phone records and documents. She wants Cosby to do the same.<ref name=Contand_sues_Castor_pretrial_hearing>{{cite news|url=http://nbc25news.com/news/entertainment/cosby-lawyer-asked-to-detail-donation-ties-to-ex-prosecutor|title=Cosby lawyer asked to detail donation, ties to ex-prosecutor|publisher=25News|date=March 18, 2016|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> At a pretrial hearing on April 15, 2016, a judge ruled that Constand is entitled to any documents shared between Castor and Cosby's attorneys.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/breaking/ct-bill-cosby-laywer-emails-20160415-story.html|title=\nBill Cosby's lawyer must show accuser his emails with ex-prosecutor|work=Chicago Tribune|date=April 16, 2016|accessdate=August 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Bill Cosby vs. Beverly Johnson===\n\nOn December 21, 2015, Cosby sued supermodel [[Beverly Johnson]] for defamation,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/12/21/us/bill-cosby-sues-beverly-johnson/ |title=Bill Cosby sues supermodel Beverly Johnson for defamation |last=Ellis |first=Ralph |date=December 22, 2015 |publisher=CNN |access-date=January 3, 2016}}</ref> claiming that she told a false story in a [[Vanity Fair (magazine)|''Vanity Fair'']] article.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2014/12/bill-cosby-beverly-johnson-story# |title=Bill Cosby Drugged Me. This Is My Story |last=Johnson |first=Beverley |date=November 30, 2014 |work=Vanity Fair |access-date=January 4, 2016}}</ref> This was the first time Cosby had sued a woman who has claimed assault without being sued himself first. Cosby's lawsuit accuses Johnson of lying about the incident in which she says Cosby spiked a cup of cappuccino with an unknown drug.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/12/11/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/beverly-johnson-cosby-allegations/index.html |title=Famed model Beverly Johnson says Bill Cosby drugged her |publisher=CNN |date=December 11, 2014 |access-date=April 3, 2016}}</ref> Realizing what was happening, Johnson said she screamed and cursed at him several times before Cosby dragged her out and hailed a cab for her. (No sexual contact by Cosby was alleged in Johnson's version of the event.) Allegedly, she also repeated the story in subsequent interviews and in her memoirs, released on August 25, 2015.\n\nJohnson's \"false allegations against Mr. Cosby have been the centerpiece of her attempted resurgence and she has played them to the hilt, repeatedly and maliciously publishing the false accusations in articles, interviews, and television appearances\", Cosby's lawsuit seeks unspecified damages and an injunction preventing the model from repeating her claims and requests they be removed from Johnson's memoir, which was released in August.<ref name=Cosby_Sues_Beverly_Johnson>{{cite news|url=http://www.courthousenews.com/2015/11/18/lawyer-says-she-was-barred-from-cosby-show.htm |title=Bill Cosby sues model Beverly Johnson over drugging claim |publisher=FOX 23|date=December 21, 2015|accessdate= December 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn February 19, 2016, Cosby filed a motion to dismiss his lawsuit against Johnson. His attorney Monique Pressley wrote in an email that Cosby made the move to focus on his defense in a criminal case in Pennsylvania. Pressley wrote that Cosby plans to re-file the case against Johnson before the statute of limitations expires.<ref name=Cosby_Drops_lawsuit_Beverly_Johnson>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/bill-cosby-drops-defamation-case-against-beverly-johnson-221219057.html;_ylt=A0LEV7koic9WK2sAVm8PxQt.;_ylu=X3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw-- |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323044037/http://news.yahoo.com/bill-cosby-drops-defamation-case-against-beverly-johnson-221219057.html%3B_ylt%3DA0LEV7koic9WK2sAVm8PxQt.%3B_ylu%3DX3oDMTByMjB0aG5zBGNvbG8DYmYxBHBvcwMxBHZ0aWQDBHNlYwNzYw-- |url-status=dead |archive-date=March 23, 2016 |title=Bill Cosby drops defamation case against Beverly Johnson |agency=Associated Press |date=February 25, 2016 |accessdate=February 25, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Bill Cosby vs. Andrea Constand, Constand's mother, Constand's attorneys and ''National Enquirer''===\n\nOn February 1, 2016, Cosby filed a breach-of-contract lawsuit against Andrea Constand, her mother Gianna Constand, her current lawyer Dolores Troiani, her former lawyer Bebe Kivitz and the publisher of the ''National Enquirer''. Cosby filed the lawsuit a day before the February{{nbsp}}2 criminal court hearing that included testimony from Troiani. The lawsuit seeks full repayment plus interest on \"the substantial financial benefit\". The filing states \"Despite being expressly prohibited from disclosing such information to anyone, Andrea Constand volunteered to participate and disclosed such information to the district attorney and others.\" Troiani has maintained that the settlement agreement barred Constand only from initiating criminal proceedings against Cosby and not from cooperating if authorities came to her first. Prosecutors introduced a copy of the agreement, redacted to hide all but a single sentence, at Cosby's pretrial hearing this month. That line read: \"Constand agrees that she will not initiate any criminal complaint against Cosby arising from the underlying facts of this case.\" The lawsuit currently remains under seal and Cosby's lawyers have declined to comment on the nature of the allegations in it.<ref name=Cosby_sues_for_breach>{{cite news |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20160219_Cosby_to_Constand__Give_me_back_my_money.html|title=Cosby to Constand: Give me back my money|work=Philadelphia Daily News|date=February 19, 2016|accessdate= February 19, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn July 28, 2016, Cosby filed a motion to dismiss his entire lawsuit against all the defendants.<ref name=Cosby_Lawsuit_vs_Constand_Dismissed>{{cite news |url=http://pagesix.com/2016/07/29/bill-cosby-drops-remainder-of-federal-suit-against-accuser/|title=Bill Cosby drops remainder of federal suit against accuser|publisher=Reuters|date=July 29, 2016|accessdate=July 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Bruce Castor vs. Andrea Constand===\n\nOn October 20, 2017, Bruce Castor's attorney, James Beasley Jr., announced that he plans to file a lawsuit against Andrea Constand for damages suffered as a result of the election in which he lost to Kevin Steele who is now prosecuting Cosby for the same acts Castor would not prosecute him for. In his suit he claims that Constand conspired with Steele to help him win the election so Cosby could be prosecuted.\nConstand's attorney, Jeffrey McCarron, responded by saying \"If his described basis is the reason for the lawsuit, then we do not expect it will last very long.\"<ref name=Castor_vs_Constand>{{cite news |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/cosby/bruce-castor-andrea-constand-lawsuit-bill-cosby-20171020.html|title=Ex-DA sues Cosby accuser whose case he rejected|work=The Inquirer|date=October 20, 2017|access-date= October 20, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Reactions==\n===Recalling encounters with Cosby===\n\n[[File:Bill Cosby Protest in Kitchener, Ontario (16225472401) (cropped).jpg|right|thumb|Demonstrators in Kitchener, Ontario]]\n\nColumnist [[Norm Clarke]] recalled an encounter with Cosby in the 1990s in Denver, where the comedian embraced a crowd of adoring fans but treated Clarke with contempt. Clarke wrote: \"Last week, as allegations of sexual assault mounted against Cosby, I found myself wondering why a man so beloved, here and around the globe, who had won over everyone from school kids to media, kept a Denver newspaperman at bay.{{nbsp}}... So what if he didn't want to talk to another journalist? But now I tend to think something else may have been involved. Self-preservation.\"<ref name=norm_clarke_Denver>{{cite news |date=November 24, 2014|title=Bill Cosby charmed fans in 1990s Denver |url=http://www.reviewjournal.com/columns-blogs/norm-clarke/bill-cosby-charmed-fans-1990s-denver|publisher=Las Vegas Review Journal blogs|accessdate=December 16, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nClarke related the experience of Donna Tagliaferri, who described \"a terrifying incident after meeting Cosby in the mid-1970s through tennis\" when she was in her early 20s. After playing tennis with Cosby a number of times, he invited her on a dinner date and then invited her up to his hotel room. Tagliaferri had a girlfriend accompany them. After showing them around the penthouse, \"things changed dramatically and quickly. He made it clear to me in a very aggressive way what his intentions were. He chillingly said to me, 'I will have you.' Those words are imprinted on my brain along with the evil I felt. My first thought was, 'No you will not.' Then shock took over, and when words wouldn't come a paralyzing feeling did.\" At this point her girlfriend started talking and got them out of the situation: \"I have no way of knowing what would have happened if Wendy had not been there. What I do know is his words were an assault to me never to be forgotten. And the betrayal of a friendship was staggering.\"<ref name=norm_clarke_Tagliaferri>{{cite news |date=November 29, 2014|title=Las Vegan recalls 'chilling' Cosby scene |publisher=Las Vegas Review Journal blogs|url=http://www.reviewjournal.com/columns-blogs/norm-clarke/las-vegan-recalls-chilling-cosby-scene|access-date=December 16, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nDana Kennedy, a journalist and correspondent, profiled Cosby for the [[Associated Press]] (AP) in 1992, noting that even though Cosby was at the height of his success and did not have any measurably negative publicity, he went on at length about \"why he mistrusts the press\", saying he likes to \"control\" his interviews. The AP piece reflected more on how uncomfortable the interview was than the substance of the interview itself. In 2014, Kennedy recalled that after the critical AP piece ran, Cosby sent her a cryptic package with a withered piece of fruit wrapped up in a paper towel. She noted that despite her interviews with some of the most notorious celebrities, it was Cosby\u2014during the time of his highest popularity\u2014who stood out as having a \"scary\" persona, recalling the mysterious package as something that \"has always given\" her \"the creeps\". It was her remembrance of \"how intimidating and menacing\" Cosby was during that experience that led her to believe the stories of the women who were accusing Cosby.<ref name=dana_kennedy>{{cite web |date=November 19, 2014|title=Bill Cosby didn't rape me but what he did has always given me the creeps |publisher=Raw Story|url=http://www.rawstory.com/2014/11/bill-cosby-didnt-rape-me-but-what-he-did-has-always-given-me-the-creeps/|access-date=November 17, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nActor [[Malcolm-Jamal Warner]], who played Cosby's son Theo on ''[[The Cosby Show]]'', stated, when asked about Cosby's state of mind since Cosby was charged with sexual assault on December 30, that he was reluctant to divulge details of their personal conversations. \"He's doing alright. That part I really don't feel comfortable talking about because we've always had a close personal relationship,\" Warner said. \"He's always been very, very good to me. Our personal conversations I tend to keep personal.\"<ref>{{cite web|first=Anita |last=Bennett |url=http://www.thewrap.com/malcolm-jamal-warner-talks-bill-cosby-fallout-there-are-financial-repercussions-exclusive-video/ |title=Malcolm-Jamal Warner Talks Bill Cosby Fallout |publisher=Thewrap |date=January 28, 2016 |accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Defenses of Cosby===\n\nIn 2014, [[Camille Cosby]], who married Cosby in 1964 when she was 19, released a statement supporting her husband, describing him as a victim of unvetted accusations: \"The man I met, and fell in love with, and whom I continue to love, is the man you all knew through his work. He is a kind man{{nbsp}}... and a wonderful husband, father and friend.\"<ref name=Karimi >{{cite news |last=Karimi |first=Faith |date=December 19, 2015 |title=Bill Cosby's lawyers fight subpoena against his wife, Camille Cosby |publisher=CNN |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/12/19/us/bill-cosby-deposition-subpoena-camille-cosby/ |access-date=December 26, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn a January 2015 ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine article about why black women should stop defending Cosby, actress [[Phylicia Rashad]] is quoted defending him: \"What you're seeing is the destruction of a legacy. And I think it's orchestrated. I don't know why or who's doing it, but it's the legacy. And it's a legacy that is so important to the culture.\"<ref name=\"Time_Jones\" >{{cite news |last=Jones |first=Feminista |date=January 9, 2015 |title=Why Black Women Are Jumping to Bill Cosby's Defense\u2014and Why They Should Stop |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |url=http://time.com/3661669/bill-cosby-allegations-black-women-defense/ |access-date=December 26, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn a July 2015 ''USA Today'' article about how the actors of ''The Cosby Show'' responded to the allegations, [[Keshia Knight Pulliam]] of the cast stated \"All I can speak to is the man I know and I love the fact that he has been such an example [and] you can't take away from the great that he has done, the millions and millions of dollars he has given back to colleges and education, and just what he did with the Cosby Show and how groundbreaking that was. The Cosbys, we were the first family that no matter what race, religion, you saw yourself in\", further addressing the charges against Cosby. \"At the end of the day they are allegations{{nbsp}}... I don't have that story to tell.\"<ref name=McDermott >{{cite news |last=McDermott |first=Maeve |date=July 21, 2015 |title=Where do the Huxtables stand on Bill Cosby? |work=[[USA Today]] |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2015/07/21/bill-cosby-scandal-what--huxtables-think/30464151/ |access-date=December 29, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, comedian [[Damon Wayans]] attacked the accusers, calling them \"un-rape-able\", and defended Cosby by stating, \"It's a money hustle.\"<ref name=\"Puente Wayans\" >{{cite news |last=Puente |first=Maria |date=September 8, 2015 |title=Damon Wayans attacks Cosby accusers as 'un-rape-able', won't back down |work=[[USA Today]] |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/2015/09/08/damon-wayans-defends-remarks-doesnt-believe-bill-cosby-accusers/71891570/ |access-date=December 26, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn December 2015, actor and comedian [[Eddie Griffin]] suggested that Cosby was the victim of a conspiracy to destroy his image and that several other prominent African-American men had been victims of similar conspiracies.<ref>{{cite news|last=Howard|first=Adam|date=December 31, 2015|title= Eddie Griffin defends Cosby, alleges 'systematic effort to destroy' black male stars|publisher=MSNBC|url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/comedian-eddie-griffin-defends-cosby-sites-systematic-effort-destroy-black-male-entertainers|access-date=December 31, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' columnist [[Clarence Page]] writes that the most popular conspiracy theory regarding the allegations involves Cosby being \"[punished] by the powers-that-be for [his] attempts to buy NBC in the 1990s\". Page wrote that the conspiracy doesn't explain why the conspirators waited so long to bring forth the accusations, with the scandal unfolding many years after Cosby abandoned the purchase. [[Dick Gregory]] was a supporter of this theory.<ref>{{cite news|last=Page|first=Clarence|date=June 20, 2017 |title=Column: Conspiracy theories fail to salvage Bill Cosby's legacy |work=Chicago Tribune|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/page/ct-bill-cosby-trial-conspiracy-theories-page-perspec-0621-md-20170620-story.html|access-date=June 23, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Defenders change their minds====\n\nTwo notable people who had previously defended Cosby, and believed in his innocence, changed their minds. American actress and talk show host [[Whoopi Goldberg]] and [[Joseph C. Phillips]] (a ''Cosby Show'' regular for three years) each made public statements on July 15, 2015. Goldberg said, \"If this is to be tried in the court of public opinion, I got to say all of the information that's out there kind of points to guilt.\" In an interview Goldberg had a message for Cosby: \"It looks bad, Bill. Either speak up or shut up.\"<ref name=France_Goldberg/> Goldberg had received threats for staunchly standing by Cosby.<ref name=France_Goldberg >{{cite news |last=France |first=Lisa Respers |date=July 15, 2015 |title=Whoopi Goldberg changes stance on Bill Cosby |publisher=CNN |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/07/14/entertainment/whoopi-goldberg-bill-cosby-feat/index.html |accessdate=July 15, 2015 }}</ref> Goldberg, in the form of a question, referred to Cosby as a \"serial rapist\" and questioned why he was still on the streets.<ref name=Goldberg_serial_rapist /> Phillips was more direct in a separate comment from Goldberg, saying \"Of course Bill Cosby is guilty!\"<ref name=France_Phillips >{{cite news |last=France |first=Lisa Respers |date=July 15, 2015 |title='Cosby Show' co-star Joseph C. Phillips: 'Of course Bill Cosby is guilty' |publisher=CNN |url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/07/15/entertainment/joseph-phillips-cosby-feat/ |accessdate=July 15, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Obama reaction===\n\nIn July 2015 PAVE: Promoting Awareness and Victim Empowerment, a nonprofit group focusing on sexual assault prevention, launched a [[We the People (petitioning system)|WhiteHouse.gov petition]], calling upon President [[Barack Obama]] to revoke Cosby's [[Presidential Medal of Freedom]] (which Cosby received from President [[George W. Bush]] in July 2002).<ref name=\"whitehouse petition\">{{cite news|url=http://thehill.com/blogs/in-the-know/247230-group-calls-on-obama-to-strip-bill-cosbys-presidential-medal-of-freedom|title=Asked About Cosby Scandal, Obama Weighs In on a Sexual Violence Discussion |date=July 8, 2015 |newspaper=The Hill |accessdate=January 29, 2016}}</ref> Later the same month, in response to a question at a news conference, President Obama said:\n{{quote|There's no precedent for revoking a medal. We don't have that mechanism. And, as you know, I tend to make it a policy not to comment on the specifics of cases where there might still be, if not criminal, then civil, issues involved. ''[long pause]'' I'll say this, if you give a woman, or a man for that matter, without his or her knowledge, a drug, and then have sex with that person without consent, that's rape. And I think this country, any civilized country, should have no tolerance for rape.<ref name=\"nytob\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/16/us/obama-wades-into-growing-sexual-scandal-surrounding-bill-cosby.html|title=Asked About Cosby Scandal, Obama Weighs In on a Sexual Violence Discussion |last=Shear |first=Michael |date=July 16, 2015 |work=[[The New York Times]] |accessdate=July 16, 2015}}</ref>}}\n\n===Cosby's response===\n\nAfter Tamara Green, one of the witnesses in Andrea Constand's case, re-told her story to ''[[Newsweek]]'' in February 2014, Cosby's publicist David Brokaw issued a statement at the time calling Green's story a \"10-year discredited accusation that proved to be nothing at the time, and is still nothing.\"<ref name=newsweek_tamara_green>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsweek.com/tamara-green-talks-about-bill-cosby-228495|title=Tamara Green Talks About Bill Cosby|work=Newsweek|date=February 7, 2014|accessdate=September 25, 2015}}</ref> When the sexual assault claims against Cosby exploded at the end of 2014, denials by Brokaw and other Cosby representatives became even more vehement, with lawyer Martin Singer calling all the allegations \"unsubstantiated, fantastical stories{{nbsp}}... [that] have escalated past the point of absurdity\".<ref name=people_singer_statement>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/article/bill-cosby-rape-laywer-statement-martin-singer|title=Bill Cosby's Lawyer Speaks Out: The Media Vilification Has to Stop|work=People|date=November 21, 2014|accessdate=September 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nWhen Dickinson came forward in November 2014 to accuse Cosby of raping her in 1982, Singer issued a denial on behalf of Cosby, saying, \"Janice Dickinson's story accusing Bill Cosby of rape is a lie.\"<ref name=variety_dickinson_lie>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/bill-cosby-lawyer-disputes-janice-dickinsons-rape-claim-1201360149/|title=Bill Cosby Lawyer Disputes Janice Dickinson's Rape Claim|work=Variety|date=November 19, 2014|accessdate=September 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAround the time of these interviews, Cosby's lawyers began sending sharply worded letters to publications that wrote about the sexual assault allegations, threatening them with legal action and using phrases like \"proceed at your own peril\" if they published certain stories.<ref name=lawyer_threats>{{cite news |date=November 19, 2014|title=Bill Cosby's new lawyer to Buzzfeed: 'You proceed at your own peril' |newspaper=The Washington Times |url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2014/nov/19/bill-cosbys-new-lawyer-to-buzzfeed-you-proceed-at-/|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> News outlets published the threatening letters from Cosby's attorneys.\n\nIn November 2014, one of Cosby's lawyers, John Schmitt, released a statement reading, \"Over the last several weeks, decade-old, discredited allegations against Mr. Cosby have resurfaced. The fact they are being repeated does not make them true. Mr. Cosby does not intend to dignify these allegations with any comment.\" This statement was also posted to the front page of Cosby's official website.<ref name=johnschmitt_lawsuit>{{cite news|url=http://www.rtlnieuws.nl/boulevard/entertainment/advocaat-van-bill-cosby-aangeklaagd|title=Advocaat van Bill Cosby aangeklaagd|date=November 16, 2015|accessdate=November 16, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSubsequent to his arraignment on three felony charges based on the Constand case, Cosby tweeted the following message on December 30, 2015, using his Twitter account: \"Friends and fans, Thank You {{sic}}.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Bill Cosby Tweets 'Thank You' to Friends, Family |last=Jacobo |first=Julia |date=December 31, 2015 |publisher=ABC News |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/bill-cosby-tweets-friends-family/story?id=36040551 |accessdate=May 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Interviews====\n\nCosby was asked directly about Buress's comments and the resulting fallout in two November 2014 interviews, which were originally intended to be about a new art exhibit at the Smithsonian that featured his private collection of African American art. In an [[NPR]] interview on November 15, 2014, reporter [[Scott Simon]] said: \"This question gives me no pleasure, Mr. Cosby, but there have been serious allegations raised about you in recent days.\" Cosby became silent, leading to an awkward radio exchange in which Simon verbally described Cosby's actions to listeners: \"you're shaking your head no.\" Simon continued asking Cosby to comment on the allegations before finally wrapping up the interview with no further communication from Cosby.<ref name=npr_cosby_interview>{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2014/11/15/364297097/in-npr-interview-bill-cosby-declines-to-discuss-assault-allegations|title=In NPR Interview, Bill Cosby Declines To Discuss Assault Allegations|publisher=NPR|date=November 15, 2014|accessdate=September 29, 2015}}</ref> In a November 6, 2014, interview with Associated Press reporter Brett Zongker, Cosby appeared visibly rattled by unexpected Buress questions and told Zongker, \"No, no, we don't answer that.\" In the following recorded minutes, Cosby repeatedly attempted to get Zongker to confirm that the AP would edit out the Buress questions, implying that Zongker's \"integrity\" and ability to be a \"serious reporter\" would be compromised if that portion of the interview was not \"scuttled\". When Zongker failed to guarantee this request, Cosby turned to his off-camera publicist David Brokaw and told him to get on the phone with Zongker's editors \"immediately\". When the interview was first released on November 10, the Buress questions had indeed been omitted. However, after the allegations continued to gain new traction, including a new accusation from Janice Dickinson, the AP decided to release footage of the full exchange on November 19.<ref name=ap_cosby_interview>{{cite news |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/xx_factor/2014/11/20/bill_cosby_ap_video_why_did_the_news_organization_suppress_it_for_more_than.html |title=Why Did the AP Suppress the Sexual Assault Portion of Its Bill Cosby Interview? |publisher=Slate |date=November 20, 2014|accessdate=September 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn a November 21, 2014, ''[[Florida Today]]'' interview, Cosby stated: \"I know people are tired of me not saying anything, but a guy doesn't have to answer to innuendos. People should fact check. People shouldn't have to go through that and shouldn't answer to innuendos.\"<ref name=Nunez >{{cite news |last=Nunez |first=Mike |date=November 22, 2014 |title=Bill Cosby to FLORIDA TODAY: I won't mention allegations |publisher=[[Florida Today]] |url=http://www.floridatoday.com/story/news/local/2014/11/21/bill-cosby-to-florida-today-i-wont-mention-allegations/19367957/ |accessdate=December 6, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==Fallout==\n\nNumerous institutions, colleges, universities, businesses, and broadcast networks have severed ties with Cosby as a result of the allegations.\n\nCosby's honorary degrees have been the subject of controversy. It is estimated that the comedian received more than 60 honorary degrees between 1985 and 2014,<ref name=nytimes_60degrees>{{cite news |date=October 6, 2015|title=To Revoke or Not: Colleges That Gave Cosby Honors Face a Tough Question |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/07/arts/television/to-revoke-or-not-colleges-that-gave-cosby-honors-face-a-tough-question.html|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> many of which were conferred after Cosby admitted to funneling money to mistress Shawn Upshaw in the 1990s, was accused of sexually assaulting Lachele Covington in 2000, and faced a sexual abuse lawsuit in 2005 by Andrea Constand with 13 other alleged victims prepared to come forward. Nevertheless, Cosby continued to collect honorary degrees, up until [[Boston University]] granted the honor to him in May 2014.<ref name=boston_degree>{{cite web |date=May 2014|title=BU to Confer Honorary Degree on Bill Cosby |publisher=Boston University |url=http://www.bu.edu/bostonia/2014/bu-to-confer-honorary-degree-on-bill-cosby/|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> The [[University of Arizona]] was still in discussions as late as November 2014 to award a degree to Cosby in 2015.<ref name=ua_degree>{{cite news |date=October 24, 2015|title=UA president proposed honorary degree for Bill Cosby|url=http://tucson.com/news/local/education/ua-president-proposed-honorary-degree-for-bill-cosby/article_f8f545ac-681f-540a-9d58-2a86744f4841.html|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nHowever, as the Cosby controversy continued to unfold, there was an increasing movement to draw attention to sexual violence on college campuses, with growing criticism that the bureaucracy of higher education led to a culture where sexual crimes were not taken seriously. ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine referred to the movement in 2014 as a \"revolution against campus sexual assault\".<ref name=campusassault_nymag>{{cite news |date=September 21, 2014|title=Meet the College Women Who Are Starting a Revolution Against Campus Sexual Assault |work=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |url=http://nymag.com/thecut/2014/09/emma-sulkowicz-campus-sexual-assault-activism.html|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> It became so prevalent that Vice President [[Joe Biden]] released an op-ed in 2015 to combat the issue.<ref name=biden_oped>{{cite web |date=November 9, 2015|title=Vice President Joe Biden Op-Ed: It's On Us to Stop Campus Sexual Assault |publisher=The White House |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2015/11/09/vice-president-joe-biden-op-ed-its-us-stop-campus-sexual-assault|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> It was against this backdrop that numerous colleges and universities began to sever their ties with Cosby, with an unprecedented number of them rescinding his honorary degrees.\n\nWhen announcing their condemnation of Cosby, many universities used the opportunity to voice strong no-tolerance policies of sexual violence of any kind. [[Brown University]] said Cosby's alleged actions were \"particularly troubling as our university community continues to confront the very real challenges of sexual violence on our campus and in society at large.\"<ref name=\"Brown rescinds\" /> In [[Baylor University]]'s statement announcing Cosby's rescinded degree, it added, \"Through the efforts of our [[Title IX]] Office, we are encouraging victims to report acts of interpersonal and sexual violence, and making sure those suffering from the effects of such acts are provided the necessary support and services to feel safe and be academically successful.\"<ref name=Baylor_University_Honorary_Degree />\n\nAfter more than 20 institutions rescinded Cosby's degrees, several others refused to do so, often citing their policy never to rescind anyone's degree for any reason. Most of these schools nevertheless included statements abhorring Cosby's conduct.<ref name=gw_not_rescinding>{{cite news |date=November 10, 2015|title=George Washington University Declines to Rescind Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree|url=http://www.nbcwashington.com/news/local/GW-University-Declines-To-Rescind-Bill-Cosbys-Honorary-Degree-345297472.html|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=smu_paulquinn>{{cite web |date=October 29, 2015|title=Why SMU, Paul Quinn College will not rescind honorary degrees given to Bill Cosby|url=http://thescoopblog.dallasnews.com/2015/10/why-smu-paul-quinn-college-will-not-rescind-honorary-degrees-given-to-bill-cosby.html|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n[[University of Pennsylvania]] received some of the greatest backlash when it announced it would not rescind Cosby's honorary degree because of university policy. It made no comment to the fact that Penn had actually previously rescinded two other honorary degrees.<ref name=penn_not_rescinding>{{cite web |date=November 6, 2015 |title=Despite 'deeply troubling' allegations, Penn will not revoke Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://www.thedp.com/article/2015/11/bill-cosby-honorary-degree-not-rescinded-by-penn|accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> ''Philadelphia'' magazine published an op-ed titled \"Penn, Are You Serious About Not Revoking Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree?\" summarizing, \"On a campus where 27 percent of women report being sexually assaulted, the hesitation is unacceptable.\"<ref name=penn_oped>{{cite web |date=November 10, 2015 |title=Penn, Are You Serious About Not Revoking Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree?|url=http://www.phillymag.com/news/2015/11/10/penn-revoke-bill-cosby-honorary-degree/ |accessdate=November 17, 2015 }}</ref> University of Pennsylvania eventually rescinded Cosby's honorary degree in February 2018.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Saul|first1=Stephanie|title=University of Pennsylvania Takes Away Steve Wynn's Honors. And Bill Cosby's, Too.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/01/us/penn-wynn-cosby-metoo.html?smid=fb-nytimes&smtyp=cur|accessdate=Feb 1, 2018|publisher=New York Times}}</ref>\n\n===Institutions sever ties===\n\nIn November 2014, colleges and universities with ties to Cosby began removing their affiliations with him. The [[University of Massachusetts Amherst]], one of Cosby's [[alma maters]], asked Cosby to step down as an honorary co-chairman of the university's fundraising campaign. The [[Berklee College of Music]], which had previously awarded Cosby with an honorary degree, got rid of a scholarship that it offered in Cosby's name. [[High Point University]] in North Carolina also pulled Cosby from its advisory board, and [[Freed\u2013Hardeman University]] rescinded its invitation for Cosby to appear at an annual dinner in December.<ref name=Mass_colleges>{{cite news|title=Massachusetts Colleges Cut Ties With Bill Cosby After Rape Claims|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/bill-cosby-scandal/massachusetts-colleges-cut-ties-bill-cosby-after-rape-claims-n257421|accessdate=July 28, 2015|publisher=NBC News|date=November 27, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn December 4, 2014, the [[United States Navy]] took the rare step of revoking Cosby's honorary title of [[Chief Petty Officer]], which he had received in 2011. The Navy released a statement saying the \"allegations against Mr. Cosby are very serious and are in conflict with the Navy's core values of honor, courage and commitment.\"<ref name=HuffPo1204>{{cite news| url= http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/04/bill-cosby-navy_n_6270718.html | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141206101835/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/04/bill-cosby-navy_n_6270718.html | url-status= dead | archive-date= December 6, 2014 |title= Bill Cosby Stripped of Honorary Title Given by Navy| work=The Huffington Post|date= December 4, 2014| agency= Associated Press| accessdate= June 29, 2015}}</ref><ref name=navytimes_revoked>{{cite news |url=http://www.navytimes.com/story/military/2014/12/04/bill-cosby-sexual-assault-navy-chief-honor-revoked/19897577/ |title= Bill Cosby's honorary chief status revoked amid controversy| work= [[Navy Times]]| date= December 4, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"navy\">{{cite news| url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/bill-cosby-scandal/navy-revokes-bill-cosbys-honorary-title-amid-sex-assault-claims-n261691|title=Navy Revokes Bill Cosby's Honorary Title Amid Sex Assault Claims|date=December 5, 2014|publisher=NBC News}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2014, amid pressure to cut long-term ties with [[Temple University]], Cosby resigned from the board of trustees.<ref name=Snyder>{{cite news| last1= Snyder| first1=Susan|title=Cosby steps down from Temple board| url= http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20141202_Cosby_steps_down_from_Temple_s_board_of_trustees.html |newspaper=Philadelphia Daily News |date=December 1, 2014 |accessdate=December 3, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn December 14, 2014, [[Spelman College]] indefinitely suspended its \"Camille Olivia Hanks Cosby Endowed Professorship\", named after Cosby's wife.<ref name=Bentley>{{cite news| last1= Bentley| first1=Rosalind|title=Spelman suspends Cosby chair in wake of growing sexual assault claims| url= http://www.ajc.com/news/news/spelman-suspends-cosby-chair-in-wake-of-growing-se/njSHn/ |newspaper=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution |date=December 14, 2014 |accessdate=July 28, 2015}}</ref> The college said it would restore the endowed professorship when its \"original goals can again be met\", but after Cosby's 2005 deposition became public in July 2015, Spelman discontinued the professorship entirely.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite news| last1= Hutcherson| first1=Kimberly|title=Spelman College discontinues professorship funded by Cosbys| url= http://www.cnn.com/2015/07/25/us/cosby-spelman-college/ |publisher=CNN |date=July 26, 2015 |accessdate=July 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nBy the end of 2014, talent agency [[Creative Artists Agency|CAA]] dropped Cosby as a client, leaving him without a Hollywood agent.<ref name=\"Cos And Effect\">{{cite news|title=Cos And Effect: Dropped Months Ago By CAA, Bill Cosby Is Un-Repped In Hollywood|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/cosby-reruns-bounce-tv-1201535254/ |work=Variety |date=July 8, 2015 |first=Whitney |last=Friedlander |accessdate=July 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn July 7, 2015, [[Walt Disney World]] removed a statue of Bill Cosby that had been featured as part of the Hollywood Studios park's \"Academy of Television Arts and Sciences Hall of Fame Plaza\".<ref name=CNN_Disney_statue>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby statue removed from Walt Disney World|url=http://money.cnn.com/2015/07/08/news/companies/bill-cosby-disney-world-statue/ |work=Variety |date=July 8, 2015 |first=Chris |last=Isidore |accessdate=July 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn mid-July 2015, after enormous public pressure to remove art work owned by Cosby, the Smithsonian's [[National Museum of African Art]] decided to post a disclaimer reminding visitors that an exhibition featuring Cosby's art collection is about the artists, not a tribute to the embattled comedian.<ref name=Smithsonian>{{cite news|title=Smithsonian posts sign telling visitors exhibit featuring Bill Cosby's art collection is not a tribute to comic battling mounting allegations of sex abuse|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3162655/Smithsonian-posts-sign-telling-visitors-exhibit-featuring-Bill-Cosby-s-art-collection-not-tribute-comic-battling-mounting-allegations-sex-abuse.html |work=Daily Mail |date=July 15, 2015 |location=London |accessdate=July 15, 2015}}</ref> The critically panned show, which had been planned since 2012 and partly underwritten by $716,000 in tax-deductible donations to the museum by Bill and Camille Cosby (who sits on the NMAA's board), is titled \"Conversations\" and includes 62 works lent by the couple. It ran until January 24, 2016.<ref name=Knight6Nov>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-ca-cm-bill-cosby-museum-african-notebook-20151108-column.html|title=Bill Cosby art collection: How the National Museum of African Art shot itself in the foot|work=Los Angeles Times|date=November 6, 2015|first=Christopher|last=Knight|accessdate=January 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn July 20, 2015, it was announced that Cosby would no longer appear in the upcoming documentary ''Painted Down'', about the history of African American stuntmen in film and television. Cosby is credited with helping to create the [[Black Stuntmen's Association]] in 1967. Producer Nonie Robinson claimed, \"We were the last project standing behind him,\" but said that pulling him from the documentary was \"the right thing to do in light of the recent court deposition being made public.\" At the same time, The Black Stuntmen's Association removed a tribute to Cosby on its website.<ref name=stuntman>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby Cut From Film About Black Stuntmen; Was \"Last Project Standing Behind Him\", Director Says|url=http://deadline.com/2015/07/bill-cosby-cut-from-painted-down-documentary-white-stuntmen-wearing-blackface-1201482313/ |publisher=Deadline |date=July 20, 2015 |accessdate=July 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn July 23, 2015, [[Simon & Schuster]] confirmed to the Associated Press that it would not be releasing a paperback version of the Cosby-approved 2014 biography ''Cosby: His Life and Times'', which gained criticism for not addressing the then-few public sexual assault allegations against Cosby.<ref name=Whitaker>{{cite news|title=Cosby biographer Mark Whitaker says he was wrong to exclude rape allegations from book|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/11/26/cosby-biographer-mark-whitaker-says-he-was-wrong-to-exclude-rape-allegations-from-book/ |work=The Washington Post |date=November 26, 2014 |accessdate=July 28, 2015}}</ref> The publisher also pulled celebrity endorsements for the book after David Letterman and Jerry Seinfeld reportedly asked to distance themselves from the biography.<ref name=independent_bio_pulled>{{cite news |title=Bill Cosby biography pulled as comedian accused of sexual assaults faces civil suit |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/bill-cosby-biography-pulled-as-comedian-accused-of-sexual-assaults-faces-civil-suit-10411752.html |work=The Independent |date=July 23, 2015 |location=London |first=Tim |last=Walker |accessdate=July 28, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn July 23, 2015, according to the ''[[Philadelphia City Paper]]'', a \"Father's Day\" mural depicting Cosby, [[Nelson Mandela]], and [[Desmond Tutu]], was scheduled for removal. It was painted over after being defaced with graffiti reading \"rapist\" and \"dude with ludes\", referencing the recently unsealed 2005 deposition in which the comedian admitted to obtaining Quaaludes to give to women with the intention of having sex with them. The [[Mural Arts Program]] was already intending to remove the mural, but rapidly accelerated the removal due to pressure.<ref name=thewrap_mural_wiped>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby Mural Wiped From Philadelphia After Comedian Tagged as a 'Rapist'|url=http://www.thewrap.com/bill-cosby-mural-wiped-from-philadelphia-after-comedian-was-tagged-as-a-rapist/ |publisher=[[The Wrap]] |date=July 24, 2015 |accessdate=July 29, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn August 17, 2015, [[New York University]]'s free 12-week film program for high school students cut all ties with Cosby. NYU had previously named the program \"William H. Cosby Future Filmmakers Workshop\". NYU has since removed Cosby's name from the Future Filmmakers program and deleted the webpage containing program information. \"The workshops will be continuing, but Cosby's name has been removed{{nbsp}}... in light of recent events,\" NYU spokesperson Matt Nagel told ''[[NYU Local]]'', in an August 28 email.<ref name=NYU_Filmakers_workshop>{{cite news|title=NYU Removes Cosby Name From High School Film Workshop|url=http://nyulocal.com/on-campus/2015/09/01/nyu-bill-cosby-film-workshop/ |publisher=NYU Local |date= August 28, 2015 |first=Kelly |last=Weill |accessdate=September 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn September 2, 2015, a portrait of Cosby made from seeds sparked outrage from attendees at the [[Minnesota State Fair]] held at the Agriculture Horticulture Building in Minnesota. Artist Nick Rindo made the crop portrait of Cosby from a type of seeds called [[rapeseed]]. He accompanied the Cosby portrait with a small card, explaining that it was made from rapeseed, but one of the staff taped over the word rapeseed. Due to the outrage, it was taken down after a day of display.<ref name=Rapeseed_Portrait>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby portrait in 'rapeseed' pulled from State Fair|url=http://www.twincities.com/statefair/ci_28734408/bill-cosby-portrait-rapeseed-pulled-from-state-fair |work=St. Paul Pioneer Press |date= August 31, 2015 |first=Marino |last=Eccher |accessdate=December 31, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn September 11, 2015, [[Central State University]], a historically black college to which Cosby has donated over $2 million, officially permanently removed Cosby's name from the Camille O. & William H. Cosby Communications Center and renamed it the CSU Communications Center. The school had been temporarily covering Cosby's name since July while it made a final decision.<ref name=Associated_Press_removed_CSU>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's Name Removed From Black Ohio University Building|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6693327/bill-cosby-name-removed-from-black-ohio-central-state-university-building |agency=Associated Press |date=September 11, 2015 |accessdate=September 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn October 7, 2015, [[Temple University]] announced that it would be further distancing itself from Cosby by replacing the vacated seat he resigned from in December 2014 with Temple alumnus and NBC correspondent [[Tamron Hall]]. The board was expected to vote on this on October 13, 2015. Hall was expected to take her seat on the board in December.<ref name=Cosby_Replaced_Temple>{{cite news |title=Temple trustees vote next week on naming NBC's Tamron Hall to board seat vacated by Bill Cosby |url=http://www.canada.com/business/temple+trustees+vote+next+week+naming+nbcs+tamron+hall+board+seat/11422029/story.html |agency=Associated Press |date=October 7, 2015 |accessdate=October 7, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160423211251/http://www.canada.com/business/temple+trustees+vote+next+week+naming+nbcs+tamron+hall+board+seat/11422029/story.html |archivedate=April 23, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nOn November 19, 2015, [[Central High School (Philadelphia)|Central High School's]] alumni board voted to remove Cosby from its Hall of Fame. Board president Jeffrey Muldawer said the decision was made to \"eliminate an issue\" that was distracting from its mission. He says some board members did not feel comfortable holding Cosby up as a role model for children. Muldawer says Cosby's removal does not reflect an opinion about the allegations. Cosby attended Central only for part of his freshman year. He was inducted in 1998.<ref name=California_State_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby's honorary degree at Cal Poly Pomona revoked|url=http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/Bill-Cosby-s-honorary-degree-at-Cal-Poly-Pomona-6647546.php |work=The Star-Ledger |date=November 21, 2015 |accessdate=November 21, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn January 20, 2016, [[Hampton University]], a historically black college, announced the removal of Cosby from its board of trustees due to allegations of multiple sexual assaults: \"For decades, Bill Cosby supported Hampton University as an institution of higher education, including serving on its board of trustees. He no longer serves on the board.\"<ref name=\"Hampton_U-Removes_Cosby_Board\">{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby no longer on Hampton Univ. board of trustees|url=http://www.13newsnow.com/story/news/local/2016/01/20/bill-cosby-no-longer-hampton-univ-board-trustees/79053812/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160122114115/http://www.13newsnow.com/story/news/local/2016/01/20/bill-cosby-no-longer-hampton-univ-board-trustees/79053812/|url-status=dead|archive-date=January 22, 2016 |publisher=13News Now |date=January 20, 2016 |accessdate=January 20, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 31, 2016, the [[National Museum of African American History and Culture]], announced that they would be addressing Cosby's sexual assault allegations in its exhibit. Initially the museum said it would not, but after enormous public pressure it changed its decision. The museum, which opens September 24, will include the cover of a comedy album by the Philadelphia-native Cosby and a comic book from his pioneering TV drama ''[[I Spy (1965 TV series)|I Spy]]'' as part of its exhibit on black entertainers and artists.<ref name=NationalMuseum_Cosby_addressed>{{cite news|url=http://www.phillyvoice.com/smithsonian-to-acknowledge-cosby-allegations-at-ne/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160403060308/http://www.phillyvoice.com/smithsonian-to-acknowledge-cosby-allegations-at-ne/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 3, 2016 |title=Smithsonian to acknowledge Bill Cosby sex assault allegations at new museum |publisher=Philly Voice |date=March 31, 2016 |accessdate=March 31, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, [[Ben's Chili Bowl]] painted over a large mural of Bill Cosby, Barack Obama and other celebrities. The restaurant's owners stated the makeover had nothing to do with the allegations against the comedian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/national-international/Bens-Chili-Bowl-Paints-Over-Bill-Cosby-Mural-411910915.html|title=DC Restaurant Paints Over Bill Cosby Mural|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"Ben's_Deletes_Cosby\">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/local/wp/2017/01/26/bens-chili-bowl-paints-over-its-mural-of-bill-cosby-and-obama/|title=Ben's Chili Bowl paints over its mural of Bill Cosby\u2014and Obama|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=January 26, 2017|access-date=January 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[Bill Cosby]] and [[Roman Polanski]] were expelled from the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] \"in accordance with the organization's Standards of Conduct\" on May 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/polanski-cosby-academy-expels-oscars/|title=Film Academy Expels Roman Polanski and Bill Cosby|author=|date=May 3, 2018|website=thewrap.com|access-date=January 20, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Rescinding of honorary degrees===\n\nMany academic institutions have rescinded [[honorary degree]]s they awarded to Cosby. Most of them cited Cosby's 2005 deposition.<ref name=\"Brown rescinds\" /><ref name=FordhamObserver>{{cite news|title=Marquette University strips Bill Cosby of honorary degree|url=http://www.fordhamobserver.com/board-of-trustees-rescind-cosbys-honorary-degree/ |work=Fordham Observer |date=September 24, 2015 |accessdate=September 24, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"FordhamObserver\"/><ref name=\"F&M\" /> Several of these institutions had never rescinded an honorary degree before,<ref name=\"MilwaukeeJournalSentinel\"/><ref name=\"Amherst\" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Board Declines Request to Revoke Cosby's Degree |url=http://oberlinreview.org/9170/news/board-declines-request-to-revoke-cosbys-degree/ |work=Oberlin Review |date=November 13, 2015 |accessdate=December 18, 2015}}</ref> or only once before.<ref name=\"Brown rescinds\" />\n\n[[Fordham University]] rescinded Cosby's honorary degree, making it the university's first in history.<ref name=\"MilwaukeeJournalSentinel\">{{cite news|title=Marquette University strips Bill Cosby of honorary degree|url=http://www.jsonline.com/news/education/marquette-university-strips-bill-cosby-of-honorary-degree-b99583730z1-329253351.html |work=Milwaukee Journal Sentinel |date=September 24, 2015 |accessdate=September 24, 2015}}</ref> Fordham said, \"The University has taken this extraordinary step in light of Mr. Cosby's now-public court depositions that confirm many of the allegations made against him by numerous women\" and that \"Mr. Cosby was willing to drug and rape women for his sexual gratification, and further damage those same women's reputations and careers to obscure his guilt, hurt not only his victims, but all women, and is beyond the pale.\"<ref name=FordhamObserver/> The next day Cosby's attorney John P. Schmitt sent a letter to Fordham University calling its statement \"so irresponsible as to shock the conscience\", and saying \"The mischaracterization of Mr. Cosby's testimony is so egregious that one can only conclude that it was written by one either unfamiliar with the testimony or determined deliberately to misrepresent Mr. Cosby's words.\" Schmitt criticized the university for an apparent effort to lend \"gratuituous support\" to defamation suits pending against Cosby, citing what he called the school's unfounded claim that the entertainer has a \"longtime strategy of denigrating the reputations of women who accused him of such actions\".<ref name=CosbyAttnyFordham>{{cite news |title=Bill Cosby attorney assails Fordham after it rescinds degree |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/09/26/bill-cosby-attorney-assails-fordham-after-it-rescinds-degree/ |agency=Associated Press |date=September 25, 2015 |accessdate=September 26, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927230241/http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/09/26/bill-cosby-attorney-assails-fordham-after-it-rescinds-degree/ |archive-date=September 27, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAlso rescinding degrees were [[Marquette University]],<ref name=\"MilwaukeeJournalSentinel\"/> the [[University of San Francisco]],<ref name=CosbyrescindHonoraryUSF>{{cite news|title=University of San Francisco Rescinds Bill Cosby Honorary Degree|url=http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/University-of-San-Francisco-Rescinds-Bill-Cosby-Degree-330150561.html |publisher=NBC Bay Area |date=September 30, 2015 |accessdate=September 30, 2015}}</ref> [[Brown University]],<ref name=\"Brown rescinds\">{{cite news|title=Brown revokes Bill Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://www.browndailyherald.com/2015/09/28/brown-university-revokes-bill-cosbys-honorary-degree/ |work=Brown Daily Herald |date=September 28, 2015 |accessdate=September 29, 2015}}</ref> [[Baylor University]],<ref name=Baylor_University_Honorary_Degree>{{cite news|title=Baylor rescinds honorary doctorate given to Bill Cosby in 2003|url=http://www.wacotrib.com/news/higher_education/baylor-rescinds-honorary-doctorate-given-to-bill-cosby-in/article_204ba1ef-403d-5390-8ebc-22cae468e1ef.html |work=Waco Tribune |date=October 8, 2015 |accessdate=October 8, 2015}}</ref> [[Lehigh University]],<ref name=CosbyrescindHonoraryLehigh>{{cite news|title=Lehigh rescinds Bill Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://thebrownandwhite.com/2015/10/14/lehigh-rescinds-bill-cosby-honorary-degree/ |work=The Brown and White |date=October 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 14, 2015}}</ref> [[Goucher College]],<ref name=\"TimeColleges\">{{cite news|last1=Berenson|first1=Tess|title=Bill Cosby Loses 2 More Honorary Degrees|url=http://time.com/4075455/bill-cosby-loses-honorary-degrees-tufts-goucher/|work=Time|accessdate=October 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Goucher rescinds Bill Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/maryland/education/bs-md-goucher-cosby-20151015-story.html|work=The Baltimore Sun|accessdate=December 18, 2015}}</ref> [[Tufts University]],<ref>[http://president.tufts.edu/blog/2015/10/15/revocation-of-tufts-awards-to-bill-cosby/ Revocation of Tufts Award to Bill Cosby], Tufts University</ref> [[Franklin & Marshall College]],<ref name=\"F&M\">{{cite web|last1=Nephin|first1=Dan|title=F&M revokes Bill Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://lancasteronline.com/news/local/f-m-revokes-bill-cosby-s-honorary-degree/article_f67175bc-76c6-11e5-9bf2-93ff4f330dcc.html|publisher=Lancaster Online|accessdate=October 20, 2015}}</ref> [[Amherst College]],<ref name=\"Amherst\">{{cite web|last1=Ivie|first1=Devon|title=Amherst College Rescinds Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree|url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/10/amherst-college-rescinds-cosbys-honorary-degree.html#|accessdate=October 20, 2015}}</ref> [[Springfield College (Massachusetts)|Springfield College]],<ref name=Springfield_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Springfield College revokes Bill Cosby's honorary doctorate|url=http://www.masslive.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2015/10/springfield_college_bill_cosby.html |publisher=MassLive |date=October 26, 2015 |accessdate=October 26, 2015}}</ref> [[Muhlenberg College]],<ref name=Muhlenburg_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Muhlenberg Rescinds Honorary Degree Awarded to Bill Cosby|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/muhlenberg-rescinds-honorary-degree-awarded-bill-cosby-34773778 |agency=Associated Press |date=October 27, 2015 |accessdate=October 27, 2015}}</ref> [[Drexel University]],<ref name=Drexel_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Drexel Revokes Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree|url=http://www.phillymag.com/news/2015/11/12/drexel-revokes-cosby-honorary-degree/ |work=Philadelphia News |date=November 12, 2015 |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> [[Bryant University]],<ref name=Bryant_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Bryant University Revokes Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree|url=http://www.golocalprov.com/news/new-bryant-university-revokes-bill-cosbys-honorary-degree |publisher=Go Local Prov News |date=November 12, 2015 |accessdate=November 12, 2015}}</ref> The [[University of Pittsburgh]],<ref name=University_Pitt_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Pitt latest university to rescind honorary degree given to Cosby|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/news/education/2015/11/13/Pitt-rescinds-Cosby-honorary-degree-university-pittsburgh/stories/201511130284 |work=Philadelphia News |date=November 13, 2015 |accessdate=November 13, 2015}}</ref> [[Drew University]],<ref name=Drew_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=N.J. college revokes Bill Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://www.nj.com/education/2015/11/nj_college_revokes_bill_cosbys_honorary_degree.html |work=The Star-Ledger |date=November 16, 2015 |accessdate=November 16, 2015}}</ref> [[California State University]],<ref name=\"California_State_Rescinds\"/> [[City University of New York]],<ref name=John_Jay_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=John Jay College rescinds Bill Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://pagesix.com/2015/11/24/john-jay-college-rescinds-bill-cosbys-honorary-degree/ |publisher=Page Six |date=November 24, 2015 |accessdate=November 24, 2015}}</ref><!--<ref name=John_Jay_Honorary_Degree>{{cite news|title=To Revoke or Not: Colleges That Gave Cosby Honors Face a Tough Question|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/07/arts/television/to-revoke-or-not-colleges-that-gave-cosby-honors-face-a-tough-question.html?partner=rss&emc=rss&_r=0 |work=The New York Daily Times |date=October 6, 2015 |accessdate=October 6, 2015}}</ref>--> [[Swarthmore College]],<ref name=Swarthmore_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Swarthmore pulls Cosby's honorary degree|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20151208_Swarthmore_pulls_Cosby_s_honorary_degree.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208202523/http://www.philly.com/philly/news/20151208_Swarthmore_pulls_Cosby_s_honorary_degree.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=December 8, 2015 |work=Philadelphia Daily News |date=December 8, 2015 |accessdate=December 8, 2015}}</ref> [[Boston University]],<ref name=Boston_University_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Boston University Revokes Bill Cosby's Honorary Degree|url=http://boston.cbslocal.com/2015/12/14/bill-cosby-boston-university-degree-sexual-assault/ |publisher=SBS Boston |date=December 14, 2015 |accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref> [[Occidental College]],<ref name=Occidental_College_Rescinds>{{cite news|title=Occidental College is the latest to revoke Cosby honorary degree|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-occidental-college-is-the-latest-to-revoke-cosby-honor-20151215-story.html |work=Los Angeles Times |date=December 15, 2015 |accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref> [[Oberlin College]],<ref name=\"Oberlin\">[http://news.oberlin.edu/articles/statement-rescinding-honorary-degree/ Statement on Rescinding Honorary Degree] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151221211443/http://news.oberlin.edu/articles/statement-rescinding-honorary-degree/ |date=December 21, 2015 }}, Oberlin College</ref> [[Haverford College]],<ref name=\"Haverford\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20160229094910/http://www.readingeagle.com/ap/article/pennsylvanias-haverford-college-rescinds-cosbys-honorary-degree Pennsylvania's Haverford College rescinds Cosby's honorary degree], Haverford College</ref> [[University of Pennsylvania]],<ref name=\"University of Pennsylvania\">{{cite web|author=Stephanie Saul |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/01/us/penn-wynn-cosby-metoo.html |title=University of Pennsylvania Takes Away Steve Wynn's Honors. And Bill Cosby's, Too. |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=February 1, 2018 |accessdate=April 10, 2018}}</ref> [[Wilkes University]],<ref name=\"Wilkes\">{{cite web|author=Eric Mark |url=http://thetimes-tribune.com/news/wilkes-university-rescinds-bill-cosby-s-honorary-degree-1.1954791 |title=Wilkes University rescinds Bill Cosby's honorary degree |publisher=The Times-Tribune |date=October 8, 2015 |accessdate=April 10, 2018}}</ref> and [[Yale University]].<ref name=\"Yale-NPR\">{{cite web|author=Richard Gonzales |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2018/05/03/607956402/yale-pulls-honorary-degree-from-bill-cosby-the-first-time-in-the-schools-history |title=Yale Pulls Honorary Degree From Bill Cosby, The First Time In The School's History |publisher=NPR |date=May 3, 2018 |accessdate=May 23, 2018}}</ref>\n\nA number of universities and educational institutions emphasized that they conferred honorary degrees on Cosby based on information known at the time of the award, and while some said they deplored recent revelations about Cosby's conduct, they lacked a policy or mechanism for revoking the honor. Other colleges refused comment, or said decisions were still pending. As of November 2015, Cosby maintained valid honorary degrees from [[Berklee College of Music]], [[Boston College]], [[Carnegie Mellon University]], [[Colby College]], [[Colgate University]], [[Cooper Union]], [[Delaware State University]], [[Fashion Institute of Technology]], [[George Washington University]], [[Hampton University]], [[Howard University]], [[Johns Hopkins University]], [[New York University]], [[North Carolina A&T State University]], [[Ohio State University]], [[Old Dominion University]], [[Paine College]], [[Pepperdine University]], [[Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute]], [[Rust College]], [[Sisseton Wahpeton College]], [[Talladega College]], [[Temple University]], [[College of William & Mary]], [[University of Cincinnati]], [[University of Connecticut]], [[University of Maryland, College Park]], [[University of Notre Dame]], [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]], [[University of South Carolina]], [[University of Southern California]], [[Virginia Commonwealth University]], [[Wesleyan University]], and [[West Chester University]].<ref name=Ivie16Nov>{{cite news|url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/10/bill-cosby-honorary-degrees.html|title=37 Universities on the Status of Bill Cosby's Honorary Degrees|date=November 16, 2015 |first=Devon |last=Ivie |publisher=Vulture |accessdate=December 30, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Broadcast networks cancel shows===\n\nOn November 17, 2014, [[Netflix]] postponed [[Bill Cosby 77|a Cosby stand-up comedy special]] after accusations surfaced that Cosby had sexually assaulted [[Janice Dickinson]] in 1982.<ref name=thestar_scrapped>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby sitcom scrapped by NBC amid growing sexual-assault allegations|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2014/11/19/bill_cosby_sitcom_scrapped_by_nbc_amid_growing_sexualassault_allegations.html |work=Toronto Star |date=November 19, 2014 |accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref>\n\nReruns of ''[[The Cosby Show]]'' and other shows associated with Cosby have also been canceled. On November 19, 2014, [[TV Land]] and [[NBC]] both ended their relationships with Cosby: TV Land announced that it was pulling reruns from its schedule and also removing clips of the show from its website,<ref name=TV_Land>{{cite news|title=TV Land Pulls The Cosby Show From Its Lineup|url=http://time.com/3596403/tv-land-cosby-show-rape-allegations/ |work=Time |date=November 19, 2014 |first=Maya |last=Rhodan |accessdate=November 19, 2014}}</ref><ref>[https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/tv-land-scraps-the-cosby-show-marathon-set-for-thanksgiving-week-1201360538/ TV Land scraps ''The Cosby Show'' marathon set for Thanksgiving week]. ''Variety'' (November 19, 2014). Retrieved November 19, 2014. \"(E)pisodes have been pulled immediately for the foreseeable future{{nbsp}}... TV Land even removed references to ''The Cosby Show'' from its website on Wednesday afternoon as the scandal accelerated.\"</ref> while NBC scrapped its plans to develop a brand new sitcom starring Cosby.<ref name=\"HuffPo1204\"/> In December 2014, the [[Magic Johnson]]-owned [[Aspire (TV network)|Aspire]] removed the two series ''[[I Spy (1965 TV series)|I Spy]]'' and ''[[The Bill Cosby Show]]'' from its lineup.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/corner/394689/magic-turns-cos-aspire-network-cancels-cosby-programming-tim-cavanaugh|title=Magic Turns on Cos: ASPiRE Network Cancels Cosby Programming}}</ref> In July 2015, broadcast network [[Bounce TV]] pulled reruns, and [[Black Entertainment Television|BET]]'s [[BET Her|Centric]] (another [[Viacom (2005\u2013present)|Viacom]] unit) ceased airing reruns.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/cosby-reruns-bounce-tv-1201535254/ |title=Bounce TV Pulls 'Cosby' Reruns, BET's Centric Yanks 'The Cosby Show'}}</ref> The show is still available on [[Hulu Plus]].<ref name=Hulu_Plus>[https://web.archive.org/web/20111120002710/http://www.hulu.com/the-cosby-show The Cosby Show], [[Hulu Plus]]. Retrieved January 19, 2016</ref> Although the series returned to Bounce TV in December 2016, the series was pulled from the network again in April 2018 following Cosby's guilty verdict.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Santi|first1=Christina|title=Bounce TV Pulls 'Cosby Show' Reruns Following Guilty Verdict|url=http://www.ebony.com/entertainment-culture/bounce-tv-pulls-cosby-show-guilty-verdict|accessdate=April 28, 2018|work=Ebony|date=April 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Legislative changes==\n===Ontario sex assault plan===\n\nIn March 2015, Ontario Premier [[Kathleen Wynne]] announced a new plan titled \"It's Never Okay\", which includes an unprecedented $41 million budget to combat sexual violence and harassment: \"The new plan was drafted in response to high-profile incidents that remain under investigation, including sexual-assault allegations against members of the University of Ottawa [[Ottawa Gee-Gees#2014\u201316 suspension|men's hockey team]], [[Jian Ghomeshi]], and Bill Cosby.\"<ref name=Csandy >{{cite news |last=Csanady |first=Ashley |date=March 6, 2015 |title=Stunning, startling ad anchors Ontario's new strategy to combat sexual assault and harassment: WATCH |newspaper=National Post |location=Canada |url=http://news.nationalpost.com/news/canada/canadian-politics/stunning-startling-ad-anchors-ontarios-new-strategy-to-combat-sexual-assault-and-harassment-watch |access-date=March 6, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Nevada sex assault law===\n\nOn May 26, 2015, Nevada Governor [[Brian Sandoval]] signed a bill that extends the statute of limitations for criminal prosecution of rape from four years to 20 years. Lise Lotte Lublin, who accused Cosby of drugging her in 1989 in a Las Vegas, Nevada hotel, testified in support of the new law and asked Nevada Assembly Member [[Irene Bustamante Adams]] to introduce bill AB212.<ref name=EURWeb>{{cite web |via=EURWeb|date=May 26, 2015 |title=Nevada Extends Statute of Limitations Because of Bill Cosby|url=http://blackamericaweb.com/2015/05/27/nevada-extends-statute-of-limitations-because-of-bill-cosby/|accessdate=May 27, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n===Colorado sex assault bill===\n\nOn September 15, 2015, Cosby accusers Beth Ferrier, Heidi Thomas, and Helen Hayes met with State Representative [[Rhonda Fields]], 18th Judicial District Attorney George Brauchler, and others at the Capitol in Denver, Colorado. There they discussed lengthening the current ten-year statute of limitations in Colorado for sexual assault. Gloria Allred, who represents most of the nearly 60 alleged victims, spoke to the gathering via [[Skype]]: \"I have been to New Jersey, and I'm not aware of any down side since they eliminated the statute (of limitations) for rape and sex assault.\" Brauchler said he does not want any victim denied a fair hearing because of Colorado's statute, but \"I don't have a magic number.\" Any change would have to be done carefully, he said, because the more time that passes between an alleged sex assault and prosecution, the harder it is for the accused to defend themselves. Fields called the cap for sexual assault arbitrary in view of the fact that most states including Colorado do not have a statutory limit on murder.<ref name=Colorado_Sex_Assault_Statute>{{cite news |last=McGhee|first=Tom|date=September 15, 2015 |title=Bill Cosby rape allegations spur effort to end Colorado's time limits|url=http://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_28817939/bill-cosby-rape-allegations-spur-effort-end-colorados|accessdate=September 15, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nOn February 11, 2016, The House Judiciary Committee voted 11\u20130 to send the bill extending the statute of limitations from 10 to 20 years to the full House. Both Ferrier and Thomas, who were alleged victims of Cosby, spoke at the hearing before the decision was made the same day. The bill was cosponsored by Rep. Rhonda Fields and Sen. John Cooke.<ref name=Colorado_Sex_Assault_Passes_to_House>{{cite news |last=Anderson|first=James|date=February 11, 2016 |title=\nCosby cases prompt Colorado bill extending time for charges|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/entertainment/articles/2016-02-11/cosby-cases-prompt-colorado-bill-extending-time-for-charges|access-date=February 11, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Presidential Medal of Freedom bill===\n\nOn January 5, 2016, it was discovered that U.S. Representative [[Paul Gosar]] (R-Ariz.) had been crafting a measure to revoke Cosby's [[Presidential Medal of Freedom]] since the July release of a 2005 deposition in which Cosby acknowledged using drugs on women with whom he wanted to have sexual relations. \"Cosby has admitted to drugging women in order to satisfy his sexual desires, and, therefore, the Federal government should not recognize Cosby with an honor like the Presidential Medal of Freedom\", the bill states. The legislation would further impose criminal penalties on anyone who publicly displays a Medal of Freedom revoked by the president, including up to a year in prison. \"To continue honoring Bill Cosby with this prestigious accolade would be an affront to women nationwide, particularly those who were victims of his horrific acts\", Gosar wrote in a letter to fellow lawmakers asking them to co-sponsor his bill.<ref name=\"Revoke_Medal_of_Freedom ?\">{{cite news |last=Morcos|first=Christina|date=January 6, 2016 |title=Republican pushing to revoke Bill Cosby's presidential medal| publisher=The Hill blogs |url=http://thehill.com/blogs/floor-action/house/264869-gop-lawmaker-plans-measure-to-urge-revoking-bill-cosbys-presidential|accessdate=January 6, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===Oregon sex assault bill===\n\nA bill in the Oregon Senate would create an exception to the 12-year statute of limitations for the most serious sex crimes\u2014including rape, sodomy and child abuse\u2014allowing prosecutors to bring charges if new concrete evidence emerges. For example, they could reopen the case if multiple victims come forward with similar allegations or if new written evidence is discovered. Senate Bill 1553 was inspired by high-profile rape cases, including the one involving Brenda Tracy, who reported being raped by four football players in Corvallis in 1998, and the one involving Cosby. Under the bill, new victims coming forward could be used as evidence to reopen a case, said Aaron Knott, the legislative director for Oregon Attorney General [[Ellen Rosenblum]]. \"While Bill Cosby is a celebrity, it's not unique to him\", Knott told lawmakers at a committee hearing on February 8, 2016.<ref name=Oregon_Sex_Assault_Statute>{{cite news |last=Kulgren|first=Ian|date=February 8, 2016 |title=After Bill Cosby and Brenda Tracy, lawmakers weigh more changes to sexual assault laws|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/politics/index.ssf/2016/02/after_bill_cosby_and_brenda_tr.html|access-date=February 9, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n===California sex assault law===\n\nOn January 3, 2016, California State Senator [[Connie Leyva]] introduced Senate bill 813, named the \"Justice for Victims Act\". This bill would eliminate the 10-year statute of limitations in California for felony sexual offenses of [[rape]], [[sodomy]], [[lascivious act|lewd or lascivious act]]s, [[Child sexual abuse|continuous sexual abuse of a child]], [[Oral sex|oral copulation]], and [[Vaginal sex|sexual penetration]]. The bill has support from Gloria Allred, the San Bernardino County District Attorney's Office and others.<ref name=California_sex_assault_bill>{{cite news|url=http://sd20.senate.ca.gov/news/2016-01-04-senator-leyva-introduces-justice-victims-act|title=Senator Leyva Introduces 'Justice for Victims Act'|publisher=California Government|date=January 4, 2016|accessdate=January 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn April 12, 2016, four alleged victims of Bill Cosby, Linda Kirkpatrick, Lili Bernard, Victoria Valentino and \"Kasey\" testified before the Senate committee. \"I wanted them to know that the system failed us,\" Kirkpatrick said. Also testifying was Attorney Gloria Allred who represents 33 of Cosby's alleged victims.<ref name=\"Allred_33_AllegedVictims\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://broadly.vice.com/en_us/article/alleged-cosby-victims-testify-against-the-rape-law-that-failed-them|title=Alleged Cosby Victims Testify Against the Rape Law That Failed Them|publisher=the Vice|date=April 14, 2016|accessdate=April 14, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn September 28, 2016, Governor [[Jerry Brown]] signed the bill into law. The law took effect January 1, 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sfgate.com/politics/article/New-Calif-law-eliminates-10-year-statute-of-9398124.php|title=New California law ends 10-year statute of limitations on rape |publisher=California Senate Democrats | date=September 28, 2016|accessdate=September 28, 2016}}</ref> It was supported by women's / LGBT rights activist [[Ivy Bottini]] and Dr. Caroline Heldman who are also involved in a campaign called #EndRapeSOL to eliminate the statute of limitations on rape in other states. Lili Bernard, Victoria Valentino and other alleged victims of Cosby have contributed to this grassroots effort.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/bill-cosby-accusers-are-fighting-to-fix-the-legal-system-that-shut-them-out_us_563cf3d4e4b0411d3070e3b5|first=Jessica|last=Samakow|publisher=The Huffington Post|title=How Cosby's Accusers Are Fighting To Fix The Legal System That Shut Them Out|date=November 11, 2015|access-date=May 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nFellow stand-up comics, including [[Dave Chappelle]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themuse.jezebel.com/what-does-dave-chappelle-have-to-say-about-bill-cosby-1793534061|title=What Does Dave Chappelle Have To Say About Bill Cosby? It's Complicated (And Convoluted)|first=Rich|last=Juzwiak|publisher=jezebel.com}}</ref> [[Judd Apatow]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/article/2015/07/21/judd-apatow-bill-cosby-tonight-show/|title=Judd Apatow slams Bill Cosby during 'Tonight Show' stand-up set|date=July 21, 2015|work=Entertainment Weekly}}</ref> [[Martin Lawrence]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/martin-lawrence-prove-stand-comedy-special-14-years/story?id=41953427|title=Martin Lawrence Has 'Nothing to Prove' in First Comedy Special in 14 Years |date=September 9, 2016|publisher=ABC News}}</ref> [[Jim Norton (comedian)|Jim Norton]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/24/jim-norton-bill-cosby_n_7138494.html|title=Jim Norton Defends Making Bill Cosby Jokes: 'He Had To Be Made Fun Of'|first=Emily Tess|last=Katz|date=April 24, 2015|publisher=HuffPost.com}}</ref> [[Bill Maher]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2014/nov/23/bill-maher-roasts-creep-bill-cosby-pull-up-your-pa/|title=Bill Maher roasts 'creep' Bill Cosby: 'Pull up your pants!' |newspaper=The Washington Times}}</ref> [[Ricky Gervais]],<ref>{{cite web|url= https://scrapsfromtheloft.com/2018/03/15/ricky-gervais-humanity-transcript/|title= Ricky Gervais: Humanity|publisher=Scraps from the loft}}</ref> [[Lisa Lampanelli]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://wtop.com/living/2015/07/comedienne-lisa-lampanelli-talks-donald-trump-and-bill-cosby/|title=Comedienne Lisa Lampanelli Talks Donald Trump and Bill Cosby|date=July 24, 2015|publisher=WTOP}}</ref> [[Jeff Ross]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/jeff-ross-roasts-criminals-10-802369|title='Jeff Ross Roasts Criminals': 10 Funniest Jokes From Comedy Central's Prison Special|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> and [[Jim Jefferies (comedian)|Jim Jeffries]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esquire.com/entertainment/q-and-a/a46450/jim-jefferies-interview-freedumb/|title=Jim Jefferies Can't Vote for the Next President, so He's Going to Tell You Some Jokes Instead|date=July 6, 2016|work=Esquire}}</ref> have commented on the allegations in their stand-up.\n\nIn the 2016 comedy film ''[[Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising]]'', a character jokes \"we got Cosby'd\" after realizing he's been drugged.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uproxx.com/movies/seth-rogen-neighbors-2-sorority-rising/|title=Seth Rogen On 'Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising' And Being The First Movie To Use 'Cosby' As A Verb|date=May 17, 2016|publisher=Uproxx}}</ref> ''[[South Park]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/11/bill-cosby-taylor-swift-south-park_n_6309590.html|title='South Park' Goes There With Bill Cosby & Taylor Swift Duet|first=Andy|last=McDonald|date=December 11, 2014|publisher=HuffPost}}</ref> ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/02/bill-cosby-jeopardy-snl|title=Watch S.N.L. Take Aim at Bill Cosby in \"Celebrity Jeopardy!\" Sketch|first=Joanna|last=Robinson|publisher=Vanity Fair}}</ref> ''[[Inside Amy Schumer]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/amy-schumer-bill-cosby-rape-trial-video-1201506615/|title=Watch: Amy Schumer Tackles Bill Cosby Rape Accusations|first=Reece|last=Ristau|date=May 27, 2015|publisher=Variety}}</ref> and ''[[Family Guy]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/family-guy-creates-cosby-show-840576|title='Family Guy' Re-Creates 'Cosby Show' Opener \"Knowing What We Know Now\"|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> also mocked Cosby for his alleged sexual misbehavior.\n\n[[Eddie Murphy]] joked about Cosby's downfall and resurrected his iconic impression of him while accepting the award for the [[Mark Twain Prize for American Humor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/browbeat/2015/11/23/eddie_murphy_s_full_mark_twain_speech_and_bill_cosby_impression_his_first.html|title=Eddie Murphy's Bill Cosby Impression Is as Good as Ever|first=Sharan|last=Shetty|date=November 23, 2015|publisher=Slate}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, when pornographic actor [[James Deen]] was accused of sexual assault by multiple women, ''[[HuffPost|The Huffington Post]]'' referred to him as \"the Bill Cosby of porn\".<ref name=THP>{{cite web|publisher=The Huffington Post|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/james-deen-rape-explainer_566063f8e4b079b2818d68f4|title=What To Know About The Sexual Assault Allegations Against James Deen|author=Hanson, Hilary|date=December 4, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2018, the Christmas song \"[[Baby, It's Cold Outside]]\" was pulled from several radio stations amid controversy that its lyrics allegedly promote sexual predation. Susan Loesser, daughter of composer [[Frank Loesser]], who wrote the song, blamed Bill Cosby for backlash against its lyric \"say, what's in this drink?\" Loesser said \"Bill Cosby is ruining it for everybody{{nbsp}}... Ever since Cosby was accused of drugging women, I hear the date rape thing all the time{{nbsp}}... I think it would be good if people looked at the song in the context of the time. It was written in 1944. It was a different time.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/bill-cosby-blamed-frank-loesser-baby-its-cold-outside-bans_us_5c09ac21e4b04046345a85e4|title=Bill Cosby Blamed For Controversy Over 'Baby, It's Cold Outside'|first=Mary|last=Papenfuss|date=December 7, 2018|publisher=|access-date=January 20, 2019|via=Huff Post}}</ref>\n\n==Impact on Cosby's legacy==\n\nJoan Tarshis, who had accused Cosby of raping her, within a ''[[Salon.com]]'' article, compared Cosby's damaged legacy to that of [[O.J. Simpson]], saying \"When you hear O. J. Simpson's name, you don't think, ''Oh, great football player''. That doesn't come to mind first. I'm thinking it's not going to be, ''Oh, great comedian''. It's going to be, ''Oh, serial rapist''.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2015/07/27/bill_cosbys_accusers_paint_a_chilling_portrait_of_the_man_and_his_legacy_i%e2%80%99m_thinking_it%e2%80%99s_not_going_to_be_oh_great_comedian_it%e2%80%99s_going_to_be_oh_serial_rapist/|title=Bill Cosby's accusers paint a chilling portrait of the man and his legacy: \"I'm thinking it's not going to be, Oh, great comedian. It's going to be, Oh, serial rapist\"|first=Mary Elizabeth|last=Williams|date=July 27, 2015|publisher=Salon}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, ''[[Ebony (magazine)|Ebony Magazine]]'' released an issue with Cosby's allegations as the cover story, discussing the importance of ''[[The Cosby Show]]'' and if it is possible to separate Bill Cosby from [[Cliff Huxtable]]. The cover depicted a photograph of The Huxtables with a cracked frame, symbolizing the show's damaged and complicated legacy.<ref>{{cite web|date=October 22, 2015|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/10/22/ebonys-cracked-cosby-show-cover-reveals-fractures-in-shows-legacy-for-black-community/|title=Ebony's cracked 'Cosby Show' cover reveals fractures in show's legacy for black community|newspaper=The Washington Post}}</ref>\n\n''[[Rolling Stone]]'' placed Cosby's concert film ''[[Bill Cosby: Himself]]'' as number{{nbsp}}8 on its list of \"The 25 Best Stand-Up Specials Of All Time\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/lists/divine-comedy-25-best-stand-up-specials-and-movies-20150729/bill-cosby-himself-1983-20150729|title=Divine Comedy: 25 Best Stand-Up Specials and Movies|work=Rolling Stone}}</ref> acknowledging the significance of the film while still saying \"Yes, it's damned near impossible to watch anything the tainted comedian has done and not think of the headlines, the heckling, the revelations and what is, by any definition, monstrous behavior.\" They also placed Cosby at number{{nbsp}}8 on their list of \"The Best Stand-up Comics Of All Time\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/lists/50-best-stand-up-comics-of-all-time-w464199/bill-cosby-w464254|title=50 Best Stand-Up Comics of All Time|work=Rolling Stone}}</ref> saying \"Bill Cosby is not likely to perform again; listening to his records will never have that gentle, sweet sense of nostalgia for anyone; and while it is impossible to disconnect the performer from the man, scrubbing his name from the annals of stand-up would be impossible.\"\n\n==Cosby's mention of drugs==\n\nIn light of the allegations of drug-assisted sexual assaults, Cosby's history of jokes about \"[[Cantharidin|Spanish Fly]]\" has come under increased scrutiny. It has been described as coming back \"to haunt him\".<ref name=Howard />\n\nIn his 1969 biographical comedy album ''[[It's True! It's True!#Spanish Fly|It's True! It's True!]]'', he talks of the male fantasy with \"Spanish Fly\" and jokes about slipping the [[aphrodisiac]] into unsuspecting women's drinks. The joke begins with a 13-year-old Cosby first hearing of the substance and ends with an adult Cosby excitedly asking about getting Spanish Fly while in Spain, only to be disappointed when a local cab driver asks him for \"American Fly\".<ref name=Howard >{{cite web |url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/cosbys-history-spanish-fly-jokes-comes-back-haunt-him#55409 |title=Cosby's history of 'Spanish Fly' jokes comes back to haunt him |last=Howard |first=Adam |date=January 14, 2015 |publisher=MSNBC |access-date=January 4, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn a 1991 interview with [[Larry King]], as part of a promotional tour for his book ''Childhood'', Cosby joked about \"Spanish Fly\", a slang term in his youth for a pill that could serve as an aphrodisiac.<ref name=Howard />\n\nIn his 1992 book ''Childhood'', Cosby devotes an entire chapter to Spanish fly, recalling how enamored he was with the concept as a pubescent boy. A young Cosby asks what Spanish fly looks like, how to give it to a girl (\"In a sandwich of somethin'?\"), and how much of it to use, to which one of Cosby's childhood friends replies, \"Soon as her clothes come off, that's enough.\"<ref name=jezebel_reading>{{cite web|url=http://jezebel.com/reading-bill-cosby-the-wit-and-wisdom-of-an-accused-se-1679809081|title=Reading Bill Cosby: The Wit And Wisdom Of An Accused Serial Rapist|author=Ellie Shechet|publisher=Jezebel}}</ref>\n\nOn January 8, 2015, in a stand-up routine by Cosby at [[Budweiser Gardens]] in [[London, Ontario]], he quipped, \"You have to be careful about drinking around me\", to a woman in the front row who reportedly was exiting to get a beverage and offered to grab him one. [[MSNBC]] and ''[[National Post]]'' journalists interpreted Cosby's joke as a reference to the drugging and sexual assault allegations against him.<ref name=MSNBC_jokes_careful>{{cite web|url=http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/cosby-jokes-you-have-be-careful-about-drinking-around-me|title=Cosby jokes: 'You have to be careful about drinking around me' |publisher=MSNBC Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/arts/bill-cosby-makes-a-joke-about-the-sexual-assault-allegations-against-him-during-his-london-ontario-show|title=Bill Cosby makes a joke about the sexual assault allegations against him during his London, Ontario, show|author=Richard Warnica|date=January 9, 2015|work=National Post|access-date=July 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Hush money payments and cover-up==\n\nIt has been reported that one of the reasons many of Cosby's accusers did not initially come forward is that Cosby gave them money in exchange for their silence. When asked in his deposition whom he wished to keep the affair from, Cosby replied \"Mrs. Cosby\".<ref name=thr_serignese>{{cite news|title=Bill Cosby Reveals Tactics for Sleeping With Women, Admits Paying Hush Money in New Documents|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bill-cosby-reveals-tactics-sleeping-809746 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=July 18, 2015 |access-date=September 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2014, former NBC facilities manager Frank Scotti told the ''New York Daily News'' that while working on ''The Cosby Show'', Cosby funneled regular payments to several women via money orders that Scotti was told to purchase in his own name. Among the women identified in receipts that Scotti preserved for more than 20 years were Shawn Thompson, Cosby's admitted mistress who later accused him of fathering her child, and Angela Leslie, who claimed Cosby made unwanted sexual advances toward her in the early 1990s. Scotti \"suspected that [Cosby] was having sex with them\". He also noted that Cosby \"was covering himself by having my name on [the money orders]. It was a coverup.\"<ref name=dailynews_scotti>{{cite news|title=Ex-NBC employee Frank Scotti claims Bill Cosby paid off women, invited young models to dressing room as he stood guard|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/bill-cosby-paid-women-ex-nbc-employee-article-1.2020464 |work=New York Daily News |date=November 23, 2014 |access-date=September 28, 2015}}</ref> Scotti also claimed that Cosby regularly took aspiring models and actresses into his dressing room and instructed Scotti, \"Stand outside the door and don't let anyone in.\" In a later interview for ''NBC''{{'s}} ''Today Show'', Scotti said he \"felt like a pimp\".<ref name=today_scotti>{{cite news|title=Ex-NBC employee says he sent money to women for Bill Cosby|url=http://www.today.com/news/ex-nbc-employee-says-he-sent-money-women-bill-cosby-1D80311460 |work=Today Show |date=November 24, 2014 |access-date=September 28, 2015}}</ref> Cosby's lawyer Martin Singer denied Scotti's accusations and said the walker-bound 90-year-old was merely seeking \"his 15 minutes of fame\".<ref name=dailynews_scotti/>\n\nIn the 2005 deposition that was made public in July 2015, Cosby admitted to making regular payments to Therese Serignese after having sex with her in the 1970s.<ref name=\"thr_serignese\"/>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Harvey Weinstein sexual abuse cases]]\n* [[Jimmy Savile sexual abuse scandal]]\n* [[Operation Yewtree]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dzB8dTVALQI Video referencing the sexual assault allegations] by comedian [[Hannibal Buress]], October 2014\n* [https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/07/18/arts/bill-cosby-deposition-excerpts.html Excerpts From Bill Cosby's Deposition in the Andrea Constand case]\n\n{{Bill Cosby}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cosby, Bill}}\n[[Category:2014 scandals]]\n[[Category:2015 scandals]]\n[[Category:2000s in the United States]]\n[[Category:2010s in the United States]]\n[[Category:2010s trials]]\n[[Category:Bill Cosby|Sexual assault cases]]\n[[Category:Sexual abuse cover-ups]]\n[[Category:Sexual assaults in the United States]]\n[[Category:Sexual misconduct allegations]]\n[[Category:Sex crime trials]]\n[[Category:Trials in the United States]]\n[[Category:Violence against women in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1004:b16b:5209:49a5:c124:bdf7:4d9", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Cosby_sexual_assault_cases"}
